	(32, 'The player function does not work. \n\nHello Amazon, how can your QC on your flagship new product be so bad?', 'Matt N4 at Drexel U', 'iTunes', 1, 'Don\'t update to NOV 29 Version', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-11 10:41:35'),
	(33, 'What a worthless junk app!! First time I come up with such a failed app. \nI have to return the echo just because the app wouldn’t work since you can’t setup the device without the app. \nShame on you amazon !!!!!!!', 'Tolgaakr', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worthless!! It doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-11 21:51:23'),
	(34, '1. Slow. Takes forever to navigate to the shopping list if your connection is less than perfect. \n2. Crappy refresh routines make the shopping list feature unusable in a grocery store. \n3. Cards sometimes show what you ask - but not always. \n4. Useless ‘drop in’ gets a button on the main screen, but the useful ‘shopping list’ takes three steps to get to. \n5. You can’t talk to this app as Alexa - for that you have to use the Amazon shopping app!', 'Horace Gumboot', 'iTunes', 2, 'Alexa is good, this app is terrible.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-12 03:26:39'),
	(35, 'Cannot login. Having my echo dot as a bullsh*t', 'Zero_mitsu', 'iTunes', 1, 'Most stupid app I\'ve ever used', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-12 04:07:51'),
	(36, 'I don’t have any main problems with app but the fact that I can’t add individual skills to a routine instead of playing my whole flask briefing is ridiculous. They really need to get on that. If that can happen then I’ll give the app a perfect 5.', 'ninirobi', 'iTunes', 4, 'It’s good but...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-12 17:32:21'),
	(37, 'No search option for music. This app will leave you playing songs over Bluetooth instead of controlling Alexa through the app. The developer should be fired.', 'Craigyas', 'iTunes', 1, 'Near Useless App.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-12 19:15:12'),
	(38, 'This app needs a lot of work. The glitches make it almost unusable! There is a screen that asks for permission to see contacts for the call/text feature, but that screen continues to pop up even after I’ve allowed them. It is not the full permission screen and has errors when you press Allow or not. The only fix I’ve found is to delete the app and reinstall it. What a waste of time! There are other glitches almost every time I use the app as well. Disappointing!', 'JenDrees6', 'iTunes', 1, 'Amazon can do better', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-12 19:29:36'),
	(39, 'Setting an alarm can be difficult because you have to tell Alexa and be very clear with the instructions. This takes A LOT of time. It would be better if we could set an alarm through the app. It doesn’t make sense why you can set reminders through the app, but not alarms and timers. It’s very time consuming and confusing. Please fix it.', 'zcmin68', 'iTunes', 2, 'Alarms', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-13 03:32:02'),
	(40, 'It’s a good thing Amazon is focusing on verbal, non-visual AI because whomever is creating these apps doesn’t know what they’re doing.  It doesn’t work.  It won’t even load passed the first permissions page.  I cannot set up our Echo now either.  Amazon products are a waste of money, time, and energy.', 'onebluehaze', 'iTunes', 1, 'The App Doesn’t Even Work!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-13 13:38:24'),
	(41, 'Can\'t get past thenew challenge.  Very disappointed', 'Dorani76', 'iTunes', 1, 'Can\'t use on ipad pro', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-13 17:25:14'),
	(42, 'You got that right, here is one star sticker for you!', 'Ralph101', 'iTunes', 1, 'Jesus is a fictional character', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-13 17:37:23'),
	(43, 'The app just doesn’t work. I got the Echo Dot brand new and it doesn’t connect to the Dot at all.', 'samsaz81', 'iTunes', 1, 'Does not work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-13 18:00:55');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(44, 'Doesn’t work most of the time.  Can’t access lists let alone anything else.  Makes Alexa far less useful as it is supposed to be an extension of her.', 'PacCoastGirl', 'iTunes', 1, 'Unreliable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 03:35:48'),
	(45, 'With these last few updates the app had additions but they didn’t mention the removal of the drop in feature or not having access to contacts through the app. Yes Alexa can still play must and tell me jokes but I can’t use it’s intercom feature anymore. I agree with other user and hope Amazon gets on improving the app because Alexa is awesome.', 'Tee Lu', 'iTunes', 2, 'Not sure what’s going on', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 04:43:46'),
	(46, 'Setting and other things won\'t load, freezes all the time', 'Nsenoyuit', 'iTunes', 1, 'Fix the app ya dumb sh*ts', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 06:30:47'),
	(47, 'Please fix.', 'eeleus', 'iTunes', 1, 'Can’t set time zone / location', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 06:44:36'),
	(48, 'This app is ok. Could look a little better and have more features but overall it works.', 'spliff1904', 'iTunes', 3, 'Needs watch app!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 06:56:10'),
	(49, 'This app constantly runs into all types of issue. Taking forever to load or not connecting to the network. 5 different times now I have had to uninstall and reinstall I.T just to update my echo dot to a different WiFi. As much I wanna enjoy this product it hasn’t been the simple seamless connection I feel I.T brags about. I shouldn’t have to do a whole set up just to connect the dot to a different WiFi. It’s a hassle', 'iosJegs', 'iTunes', 1, 'App Needs More Attention', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 16:12:04'),
	(50, 'How is it Amazon can\'t write a usable API for this app. When opening the app it takes at least 20 seconds just to get past the Alexa splash screen. When trying to use a shopping list where there is little or no cell service, it\'s unresponsive and doesn\'t seem to have a reliable off-line mode. The alarm function of the app causes the app to crash most of the time and I have to force close the app and restart it.', 'cirtbrethren', 'iTunes', 1, 'Constantly freezes up', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 16:51:21'),
	(51, 'App doesn’t let me pass the setup page. Buttons are useless on my iPhone X. This phone has been out for a while and I cannot believe this is still an issue.', 'aysunbcc', 'iTunes', 1, 'App is broken', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-14 18:49:07'),
	(52, 'Worthless app. Will not see my Echo Show despite numerous resets, so unit will be sent back as it’s a worthless paper weight.  Come on Amazon, you can do better! I think I’ll stick with Siri.', 'rorybreaker69', 'iTunes', 1, 'Can’t connect to my echo show', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-15 01:47:59'),
	(53, 'Y’all need to hire some real iOS engineers.', 'Tom73838778388282', 'iTunes', 1, 'Freezes a lot', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-15 04:36:01'),
	(54, 'It won’t open on the new iOS update', 'carsoncarroll7', 'iTunes', 2, 'Not working', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-15 05:26:25'),
	(55, 'To begin with, let me say I love my Echo and all the dots I have spread around the house.  I have converted much of my home light switches to z-wave switches, and have a Wink 2 hub.  I have z-wave plugs everywhere, and am enjoying my home automation, especially when it works with Alexa.  I also enjoy the multi-room music capability, or did when it worked.\n\nWith progressive “updates” to the app, it seems that functionality continues to step backwards.  The app now refuses to communicate with my early generation Echo (bought during the Beta-wonder if they’re trying to make me update), and now the multiroom music just doesn’t want to work.  Further, the app has taken to freezing up, especially if I try to enter the settings section of the app to figure out what’s wrong with my hardware.\n\nAs you can tell, I am an amazon fan, and really enjoy the Alexa environment; however, Amazon is not necessary for my Wink and all my remote controlled devices, and I’m close to looking into the new Google device or the Invoke.  \n\nFrustrating that something that started so strong seems to be falling fast in reliability.', 'Christian_Anime', 'iTunes', 1, 'So much potential', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-15 16:47:16');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(56, 'Have had to close and open the app far more than I should have to to reset it. Very slow and glitchy been stuck in the settings window for 10 min.\n\nDoes not connect to verizon mobile hotspot. When trying to connect to my xfinity wifi it says i need third party access but the shortcut on the app sends me to a "website unavailable" screen. Until I get a different internet provider Alexa is pretty much useless to me at this point.\n\nIt\'s like all the money/good people were used on building the physical Alexa and the task of the app was left to a couple burnouts in the basement of a old sears.', 'Boosted Honda', 'iTunes', 1, 'Slow/glitchy/awful', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-15 19:44:18'),
	(57, 'Cannot sign in at all', 'ancksks', 'iTunes', 1, 'Cannot sign in', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 05:40:58'),
	(58, 'When is the app going to be Iphone X compatible? \nKeep closing.', 'ebescobar', 'iTunes', 1, ':(', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 17:51:06'),
	(59, 'The dish hopper is not discoverable.  Was able to connect it for a couple days and then stopped working.', 'Jeschulten', 'iTunes', 1, 'Will not link with dish hopper', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 17:57:18'),
	(60, 'support iPhone X?', 'congauden', 'iTunes', 1, 'support iPhone X?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 19:57:31'),
	(61, 'On my iPhone I 6, this app has a lot of problems. It is very slow at best.  THe problems arise when revisiting the Settings area.  After the first visit, the Settings simply remains blank. The only recourse is to quit the app and relaunch. Eventually, one can accomplish needed tasks, but I always brace myself for an irritating experience when using it.  Amazon: you must be kidding with this.', 'Tcomplex', 'iTunes', 2, 'Too glitchy', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 21:16:48'),
	(62, 'I can definitely echo (pun intended) what other reviewers have said. The app seems to be losing support and features, which is pretty much the opposite of what’s supposed to happen, right, Amazon?  On top of that, we still don’t have support for the iPhone X screen size!', 'esotericmixer', 'iTunes', 2, 'Also, where is iPhone X support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 21:43:36'),
	(63, 'Really? Still? \n\nAnd the app is still sluggish.', 'JDM™', 'iTunes', 2, 'Still no iPhone X support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-16 23:08:30'),
	(64, 'The app is still not iPhone X Compliant', 'RDA1990', 'iTunes', 3, 'iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 00:35:51'),
	(65, 'Fixed the screen resolution bug. Still a bad app. Why can\'t I delete my phone # from alexa in the app and disable the "phone/intercom" feature I started setting up?\n\nWant to leave amazon feedback when a command doesn\'t work, which is about 60% of the time?  Too bad, the recent command probably won\'t show up under recent commands. Want to use alexa to turn on smart lights?  Too bad, she\'ll tell you a few things share that name when there is only one thing with that name.  Utterly worthless.\n\nWant to play a song through your echo?  Ask Alexa and hope she doesn\'t choose her own song because you can select a song in the alexa app. No, you can browse some stupid preset channels but you can\'t search a connected device, even music, and then play it through the device.', 'Originator 88', 'iTunes', 1, 'Just garbage', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 01:14:27'),
	(66, 'This campion app needs lots of work. It’s very unresponsive. Delayed or false taps all the time. No way to set favorite tunein radio stations. No way to set reoccurring weekly alarms. Skill integrations are half baked. Smart home scenes don’t include thermostat settings. Thank god for IFTTT skill otherwise my echo would have been a return.', 'The Me Tree ', 'iTunes', 1, 'Echo is great. App is not', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 01:35:49'),
	(67, 'Thought this would go well. Completely wrong. Just bad.  Do not bother.', 'TeamABCDE', 'iTunes', 1, 'Really poor', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 02:01:22'),
	(68, 'The app site states that there was an upgrade 8 hours ago, I’ve been trying to down load the app for 30 minutes. Circles, circles', 'MAJ1954', 'iTunes', 1, 'I️ can’t even load the app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 02:20:26'),
	(69, 'The app just needs to be cleaned up a little bit with tons of improvements. It’s hard to log in out of things smoothly and says my passwords are wrong half the time.', 'Peantbutter', 'iTunes', 2, 'Sorta stupid', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 03:11:31');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(70, 'I have had an Amazon Echo since they first came out. Bought a Show on its debut. Don’t waste your money. \n\nI am so sick and tired of asking for music to play from my music library to only be told it isn’t there or Alexa can’t do it. I ask it to show my my music albums. I get about two and that is it. How about all of them!  It would also be great when you did find an album you wanted to play to then be shown each track to chose the one you want it to play. No such luck. \n\nCome on tech team. Get it together.', 'BelindaButler', 'iTunes', 1, 'Liked the original. The Show not so much.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 03:38:08'),
	(71, 'It’s not that hard.', 'Fchjfgtgyf', 'iTunes', 1, 'Add iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 03:47:18'),
	(72, 'Update bugs on iPhone X', '134espi', 'iTunes', 1, 'Crashes on iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 04:25:08'),
	(73, 'What a crock. As long as you own one Alexa device you should be able to use the full version of Alexa from your phone or tablet. This does not appear to be the case.', 'thebirdman7', 'iTunes', 2, 'Can’t use Alexa even from phone or tablet', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 04:27:09'),
	(74, 'Good way to manage my echo but some iPhone X support would be nice I mean there’s only been how many updates and none of them have have included iPhone X support behind much?', 'Kennybjr87', 'iTunes', 3, 'Not bad', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 06:31:59'),
	(75, 'Come one bro, no iPhone X update. Tf are y’all doing?!', 'Johnathan Maravilla', 'iTunes', 2, 'Come on bro', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 07:20:00'),
	(76, 'Recently purchased the Dot and since the second day I haven’t been able to connect it to my WiFi. App needs improvement to be a better smart device. I think devs should focus a little more on connectivity, better and more voice commands and Skills better skills to improve the usage of the Alexa device also so people like me can recommend this device as a good one.', 'Dart-Omega', 'iTunes', 2, 'To many problems', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 09:58:33'),
	(77, 'Still not optimized for iPhone X, I’ve had to completely delete the app and reinstall twice in 1 month because it gets stuck on allowing permissions (force quit and phone restart didn’t help), it defaults to the conversation view which is useless unless that is all you care about (I use my dots for timers, adding stuff to lists, and music). The app is slow to load, slow to operate. Just pathetic. Good thing I almost never need to use the app...', 'JMZ_FLYER', 'iTunes', 1, 'Garbage', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 11:41:57'),
	(78, 'This app should be able to be a central to your home entertainment and shopping.  It is anything but that.  It’s design is very difficult to navigate and un attractive to users.  I would expect so much more from amazon.', 'Josh Vineyard', 'iTunes', 1, 'Crappy app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 12:04:51'),
	(79, 'Ghhh', 'tnchg', 'iTunes', 4, 'Good', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 12:19:46'),
	(80, 'I hope the ability to change device type will be added soon. I have a “smart plug” that has a light plugged into it, and it should be treated by Alexa as a light, so it gets turned on and off with the other lights. But currently the Alexa app won’t let the device type be changed.', 'Needs repair', 'iTunes', 4, 'I love Alexa!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 14:19:53'),
	(81, 'Good app, works great , but isn’t optimized for iPhone X so it’s ugly and small on the screen', 'Nbnewcar', 'iTunes', 3, 'No iPhone X optimization', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 15:20:30'),
	(82, 'I like to use my Echo dot to control a Bluetooth speaker.  But music controls on the Alexa app are meager.  Why can’t they be as powerful as amazons dedicated music app?   Volume control on Alexa app, for example, is a total crap shoot.', 'Drewbeeb', 'iTunes', 2, 'Music controls are poor', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 15:46:21'),
	(83, 'Kudos for having finally implemented named lists, but you still haven’t don’t anything to fix the bug that prevents people from accessing the last Bluetooth device when the list of devices reaches the bottom of the screen. It gets covered by the Add New Device button. That’s a beginner mistake in my book and is fixable in a single line of code, so get to it!!!', 'Kid Rock C', 'iTunes', 2, 'Bug fixes ... not', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 16:11:34');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(84, '...', 'Abba', 'iTunes', 1, 'Need iPhone X Compatibility!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 17:01:48'),
	(85, 'Alexa App is an interesting proof of concept, but the UI AND UX is so complicated...\nAnd basic things are hard to do (if even doable)...\nI’m not sure the ones developing the app use it in their everyday life to realize that some of the things that might be a necessity are not there...\nHope things better in the future...', 'FletcherGull', 'iTunes', 2, 'Interesting proof of concept', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 18:05:18'),
	(86, 'I’ve used it ever since it came out, on various devices and I can say their ability to produce a substandard app is excellent. They cannot even release one with X support, really?\n\nPlease fix and make this app great again!', 'calemon', 'iTunes', 2, 'Clunky and not well thought out UI', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 18:08:45'),
	(87, 'Still haven’t updated for the new phone.', 'Seangoughan', 'iTunes', 1, 'Update for iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 18:22:38'),
	(88, 'This latest update now allows scenes to be turned OFF not just ON which is a great addition. Thanks for the improvement. So far I have been able to control all my smart home devices with Alexa. My lighting, entertainment center, and thermostat are controlled by voice now with accessories for Alexa. You need to be a bit tech savvy to set everything up and make it work properly but once it’s done, it works fantastic.', 'Fxerman', 'iTunes', 5, 'Improved!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 18:35:18'),
	(89, 'I cannot even set up my Spotify account to my device because this app does not function. I can’t even use my Echo.', 'Phil Vac', 'iTunes', 1, 'Laggy', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 18:44:54'),
	(90, 'This Alexa app previously had the ability to control the echo device to do things like play music. Now it cannot do that! This app seems to be moving backwards with each update. Before that change I would have given exceptional rating but now it’s barely usable. I’m thinking of getting googles device to replace the echo because of this. PLEASE bring back the feature to control the device from the app!!!', 'tbee0003', 'iTunes', 1, 'What happened to this app?!?!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 20:29:25'),
	(91, 'This app fails to load. It\'s glitchy and changing a setting is nearly impossible.', 'JosemotaQ', 'iTunes', 1, 'Not usable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 22:51:37'),
	(92, 'Still very limited. Unable to link up with with any other smart tv devices other than Fire TV.', 'qphm', 'iTunes', 3, 'Need work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-17 23:16:27'),
	(93, 'Love the Echo but unfortunately the app is constantly freezing. I have to restart the app over and over again to try to get it to work. Trying to set up my third Echo right now and can’t even get to the setup on the app because it keeps freezing! So frustrating!', 'jmk04e', 'iTunes', 1, 'App is useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 01:37:44'),
	(94, 'The app no longer works. It freezes, sits on blank screens and won’t allow selections. I’m not sure what to do here, it literally doesn’t work.  I’m running the app on an iPhone X. Please advise Amazon.', 'Nations60', 'iTunes', 1, 'App doesn’t work anymore', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 02:26:49'),
	(95, 'I love Alexa, and have multiple Echo devices. This app isn\'t good. It freezes sometimes, it\'s slow, and it doesn\'t always respond when I tap on stuff (like to edit the address).', 'John In Arkansas', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa is awesome. App not so much.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 07:44:10'),
	(96, 'If I could give it a zero I would this update made most of my software unusable in the app. Only basic function are working now going to have to uninstall and reinstall original software.', 'swensond', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 13:34:02'),
	(97, 'Can we get the ability to remove a single contact? Please? Blocking isn’t enough and my contact list is rapidly growing.', 'PFeezzy', 'iTunes', 1, 'Contacts', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 17:20:31'),
	(98, 'Can’t connect any apps on Alexa on my iPhone. Says app support not available for things like Spotify but my boyfriend can connect to his on his Android phone. It’s an option, just not for me?', 'GnomerBoner', 'iTunes', 1, 'Totally broken', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 20:08:15');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(99, 'I no longer like the alexa and will be switching to the Google Home', 'Supercrap2003', 'iTunes', 1, 'Switching', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 20:30:52'),
	(100, 'Thank you for fixing the shopping list!', 'Goldzoe1', 'iTunes', 5, 'Shopping list', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 21:50:18'),
	(101, 'No point in stating the obvious, app is garbage right now.   I like Alexa but find it hard to believe Bezos uses this glitchy app.', '_Reef_', 'iTunes', 1, 'Does Jeff Bezos use this?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 22:04:04'),
	(102, 'Tried to link my Spotify account to play thru Alexa Echo. In order to do that you must subscribe to their Prime Unlimited music. Why am I going to pay for ANOTHER music subscription to play a different music subscription I already pay for?! Absolutely ridiculous. I will be returning and getting google home instead.', 'Fatallyyours722', 'iTunes', 1, 'Just trying to sell you their stuff', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 02:20:51'),
	(103, 'Multi Room setup button goes to the Smart Home Group instead. The setup is not right on where the buttons should be.', 'Ekit97', 'iTunes', 1, 'Multi Room Set Up', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 04:40:07'),
	(104, 'I use this app a lot and I think it’s really good but if I could also use normal skills that I have enabled when creating a routine that would be GREAT 👍🏻\n\nFor example:\nWhen I say “Alexa,drawing time” she could start playing music or if I say “Alexa,I’m bored” she could tell me how busy Disney World is or stuff like that that you can add to routines I would definitely change my rating to 5 stars if you added this feature 👍🏻😉', 'floridapuppies', 'iTunes', 4, 'Amazing but one thing...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 13:18:08'),
	(105, 'Useless videos and poor customer support surrounds this app and its products. There are no instruction manuals to be found unless you want to purchase one on Amazon in the $10 price range from people who realize Alexa is too difficult for most people to figure out. Amazon really blew it here. Bought eight echo shows to give to family. No one can figure them out and no instructions on how to use them. Apple is intuitive to use and that’s why they don’t have instructions. Alexa is not intuitive to use.  Spent time on the phone with technical support and they couldn’t figure it out themselves.  If technical support doesn’t know, how can us mere mortals figure out this mind vampire.', 'Socalducksfan', 'iTunes', 1, 'Not Ready for Prime Time', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 16:27:11'),
	(106, 'I love the concept. Telling Alexa your shopping list and then being able to retrieve them on your phone at the store. Problem is I’m never able to access it. I need to delete the app and then reinstall it before I can view my list. Very frustrating!', 'Abbeetime', 'iTunes', 3, 'Keeps Crashing', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 16:52:35'),
	(107, 'After the last update everything freezes. If I add items to my list then click home button the app freezes. I have to restart my mobile device to get the app to go to the home page', 'Beegator10', 'iTunes', 3, 'App freezes', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 22:11:26'),
	(108, 'Love my echo dot but the app is terrible. Had to change the internet password in my house. The app constantly freezes on the connections page and will not connect to the internet now. It is the only app I\'m having trouble with. Extremely unhappy with this new turn of events.', 'Mack Diesel', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-19 22:48:43'),
	(109, 'Search is not provided. Echo voice recognition is still not perfect. Why not provide search function just like Amazon Music app does?!\n\nLatest GUI change broke the volume control. It is EXTREMELY hard to slide volume control and sometimes accidentally jumps to lowest or maximum volume, risking a damage to your hearing!\n\nSince last update column bar is still extremely hard to use. Don’t these people do any alpha testing before they give us barely usable beta?!', 'Arthur Dent ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯', 'iTunes', 2, 'Buggy critical functions not working', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 00:18:45'),
	(110, 'As long as sales are good they have no incentive to really work on this app. The interface is primitive considering the amount of memory it takes up.', 'ak01q', 'iTunes', 1, 'Amazon Doesn\'t Care', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 01:57:50');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(111, '12/19:  update:   Alexa = Great.  App = Not so great.  Very glitchy.  Locks up all the time.  Feels closer to a poorly designed website vice polished app.  Haven’t seen a marked improvement for months....  if the app is having a really good day, it is functional....\n\nOld review:  App loads really slow.  When it doesn’t load really slow, it won’t load at all. Trying to set an alarm is impossible (just locks up).   Drop-in has about 50% chance of working (seems like it never gets past trying to connect via video ... which I don’t have).  I like the fact the developers are attempting to make it do more, but the more that is added, the slower it seems to perform.  Nearly lost all utility ....  please streamline and get it working at normal\niOS app speed.', 'Scan95', 'iTunes', 2, 'Getting worse', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 03:13:45'),
	(112, 'Please upgrade the tap to 11.5, it won’t connect to the iPhone 7. Can’t use my phone, I will have to cancel the subscription to unlimited music with amazon.', 'jbbihm', 'iTunes', 1, 'Tap', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 04:03:57'),
	(113, 'My husband is having issues resetting his Amazon password, so I set up the Echo Dot with mine. \n\nI can’t edit my location or address with the app, it keeps closing the option as soon as I open it. \n\nOther than that, it’s a really neat device, convenient.', 'gxen', 'iTunes', 3, 'Issues', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 04:24:22'),
	(114, 'Amazon as a big tech company, produced such a low quality app, it’s a crime. The user interface is so bad, the app is buggy, drop in call is a hit or miss, no easy way to set up repeated reminders, can’t get anything done easily. Echo has a lot of potential but this app kills it.', 'Lakeman g', 'iTunes', 1, 'What a shame', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 06:24:14'),
	(115, 'Why why why do you guys remove features and call it improvements. The static volume button in Now playing list is now missing. The Drop in feature is gone! I used be able to open the app and lower the volume or raise it so easily. I was also trying to show my doctor how easy it was to use the drop in feature and viola your developers screw it up and you can no longer drop in on any of your devices. I don’t know... if you don’t fix this crap soon I am going to start looking at google and selling the show, echo, and two dots I have now. Stop the madness and fix this ASAP!', 'Nikawat', 'iTunes', 1, 'Why', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 14:30:29'),
	(116, 'Love my echo devices, but the app doesn’t work. I have an iPhone 7 Plus and the app constantly logs me out and won’t let me sign in. When I try to sign in, it just gives me an error message. Love the app when it works. But 9 times out of 10, it doesn’t work. I have deleted and reinstalled app multiple times.', 'boxbhinkmart', 'iTunes', 2, 'Doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 17:36:24'),
	(117, 'I can not use this app to setup or make changes to Alexa. Not not IPhone friendly', 'commosgt113', 'iTunes', 1, 'Not good with IPhone', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 17:48:41'),
	(118, 'How stupid is it that you can use Alexa from the Amazon app but you can\'t use Alexa from the Alexa app?', 'Bummedhtcub', 'iTunes', 1, 'Does not work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-20 18:28:20'),
	(119, 'Lots of things don’t work and the app isn’t consistent between iPhone and iPad. Wanted to use this with new Spot, but it doesn’t look like it can adequately support the device.', 'mutantblew', 'iTunes', 1, 'Bad Job', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 06:05:02');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(120, 'New update is takes away ability to control play on echos, dots, and taps from app. When Amazon first came out with Echo I loved it and have a device in every room. Now I think it\'s suffering from it\'s popularity and Amazon can\'t handle the increased use of its service and is trying to reduce the load on its service reducing the functionality of the app and slowing the  responses from the devices. Now finding devices responding to random noise as wake word and sometimes not responding to wake word unless your a foot away and yelling, might as well use physical controls. Response to commands is deteriorating, Will give Alexa command to play song, Alexa responds with the correct title to the song but says it\'s not in the library even though I\'m looking at the song with the exact title in my library. If I keep repeating the command with Alexa giving the EXACT SAME CORRECT SONG TITLE back every time eventually instead of saying she can\'t find the song it will start playing.  This may not sound like a review of the app but the app only has a use if the Alexa AI functions usefully. Amazon needs to focus on the basic functionality and loose the mostly useless and stupid "skills."\n\nDecember 2017: constantly partial freeze so most menus items won’t open. Latest update didn’t fix.', 'Do I really have to make up a', 'iTunes', 2, 'May 2017 takes away features, can\'t control play on echos from app anymore!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 11:37:51'),
	(121, 'Please, optimize this app for iPhone X.', '@t!k', 'iTunes', 3, 'Optimize for iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 13:53:04'),
	(122, 'This version works fine for me. I mostly use the smart home controls and I have never had any connectivity issues in more than a year. The UI takes some time to get used to but it’s pretty good in my opinion. Not sure why so many complaints here because the app has improved my experience with Alexa. Spend some time exploring the settings menus and it all comes together.', 'S cell', 'iTunes', 5, 'Can’t complain.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 15:44:15'),
	(123, 'Home automation through alexa is getting better. Using Drop In feature so wife and I do not have to yell across the house. I had to buy Echo Connect to be able to dial 911, but my wife with Parkinson’s Disease can now call both me and 911 from anywhere in the house if she falls while I’m out using simple voice. Alexa can tell me the current temperature and rain accumulation from my personal weather station. I can also control lights in my house, my AC thermostats temperature and change channels on my TV. \n\nImprovements:\n- I’d like to be able to use Drop In with my iPad\n- I’d like my thermostat to tell the current temperature in my house.', 'Pdginn', 'iTunes', 3, 'Getting better as supporting devices are announced', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 16:41:52'),
	(124, 'The app is very slow after the last update! Fix the bugs ASAP!!!', 'Avishek Sarkar', 'iTunes', 1, 'App is very very slow!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 17:49:57'),
	(125, 'There is still no ability to use Alexa from within the Alexa app. When I’m on the go, this is slightly less than useful.', 'Klavmanian', 'iTunes', 2, 'Still no Alexa *in* the app..', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 19:23:44'),
	(126, 'App is fine I guess but really needs a II adjustment', 'Sethjk17', 'iTunes', 2, 'iPhone X support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 19:56:20'),
	(127, 'Still no iPhone X support. Also an error comes up every time I go into conversations. Issue is still not fixed. When are these updates actually going to fix something with this app?', 'JNazare1', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X Support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 20:37:06'),
	(128, 'The app as soon as I touch it something will play it’s to sensitive!!! And where is the volume rocker for the everywhere group!!! So you can’t change the volume on multiple devices unless I talk to it!!! Lol please fix', 'Mac Muscle Nerd', 'iTunes', 2, 'Volume Everywhere Group!!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 21:12:33'),
	(129, 'iPhone X has been out how long now?', 'kowen14', 'iTunes', 1, 'Update your app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 21:45:05'),
	(130, 'I find the UI to be very sloppy and still no added support for the iPhone X is infuriating.', 'jmancina', 'iTunes', 2, 'UI', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 21:52:44');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(131, 'You can’t ask it anything without it trying to sell you something. I would ask it to play Spotify and it would say “here’s a sample of this song the full version is on amazon blah blah blah”. I have Spotify premium just play what I ask??? Also you can’t ask it question. I returned this and bought the google home.', 'doggomommo', 'iTunes', 1, 'Useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 21:58:51'),
	(132, 'I cannot chose to connect it with Spotify it only forces me to use AMAZON music which i don\'t have account on it :(', 'FoO Ahmed', 'iTunes', 2, 'Cannot connect with Spotify', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 22:11:01'),
	(133, 'When are we ever going to get an update for iPhone X optimization?? It’s been almost two months now and this app is run by one of the largest companies in the world. You guys seriously can’t get your developers to make the few optimization changes??', 'TheAustinG', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X Support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 22:46:18'),
	(134, 'Will you please have one of your developers spend 15 minutes to add iPhone X support.', 'Joseph Saliba', 'iTunes', 4, 'iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-21 22:47:15'),
	(135, 'The phone gets very hot while I\'m in the app. The battery drops at a rate of about 2% per minute of use. It\'s extremely sluggish. The Echo itself is amazing. But the app needs a complete rebuild.', 'Robbed by the new monopoly', 'iTunes', 1, 'Most buggy app I\'ve ever installed.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 00:02:08'),
	(136, 'I continuously try to connect to my iphone hotspot i can\'t ever got it to connect - very disapointed', 'cat69henderson', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 01:14:56'),
	(137, 'Certain responses lean left and offer the manufacturers opinions rather than straight forward answers. Just give me wiki answers like all the other “AI” type devices', 'P8N_00', 'iTunes', 2, 'Less liberal please', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 01:27:00'),
	(138, 'This was WAY to hard to activate my Echo!', 'Kimi-Rose', 'iTunes', 1, 'Not so good of an app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 02:18:37'),
	(139, 'Still waiting for the ability to turn off voice feedback when you give a command. The obnoxious “Okay” after everything is absurd and needs turned off...PLEASE! I can whisper and Alexa hears me, but then she yells and then everyone is awake...so frustrating.', 'thompsonba', 'iTunes', 1, 'Still not an “update,” all seem like downgrades', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 03:28:31'),
	(140, 'There\'s a lot to dislike about this app. Nothing feels native, the organization of features is odd, and it still doesn\'t fully support the iPhone X\'s screen. That said, it manages my Echos as advertised.', 'sethlong', 'iTunes', 2, 'Still no iPhone X layout', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 03:54:27'),
	(141, 'Cannot get past “Give Amazon permissions”.  Tap allow and nothing happens.', 'jddietz', 'iTunes', 1, 'Bad update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 04:19:09'),
	(142, 'Would be nice for iPhone X compatibility and utilize full screen.', 'Samie.girl', 'iTunes', 4, 'iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 05:00:09'),
	(143, 'The app is ridiculously slow. It takes forever to load data or to show menus or to load skills or to go from one screen to another.', 'NicknamePolicyIsDumb', 'iTunes', 1, 'Slow and unresponsive', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 07:26:48'),
	(144, 'This app freezes up on the Allow access page - no matter what I opt for, its frozen :(', 'Bos922', 'iTunes', 1, 'Stuck', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 13:01:25'),
	(145, 'With all Amazon’s money it seems they could hire better software teams. At least hire some good UI and UX designers.', 'Mister Houdini', 'iTunes', 3, 'Could use a lot of improvements', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 15:36:31'),
	(146, 'Not really too happy with the style of the app. It feels very outdated but apart from that it works well', 'zeicek', 'iTunes', 3, 'Needs to be optimized for the iPhone X!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 15:44:40'),
	(147, 'The app works well, but there are times when it asks me to log in or for permissions when I’ve already done that and usually freezes on that screen. I’ve had to uninstall and reinstall the app numerous times. Hopefully, Amazon will work out the kinks since it is pushing its Echos hard for Christmas. I really like my Dot, but the app is second rate.', 'Lunatude', 'iTunes', 3, 'Unreliable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 16:12:16');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(148, 'The Conversation icon has disappeared from my iPad.  It’s still there so I am able to limit Drop In permissions but very frustrating.  Hopefully the app developers will fix this!', 'chf0815', 'iTunes', 3, 'iPad version has lost he Conversation icon', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 19:32:52'),
	(149, 'App now makes you to sign up with their messenger service if you want to use the app at all. Can\'t even use the echo as a Bluetooth speaker anymore.', 'EricCM', 'iTunes', 1, 'Do not buy an echo', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 21:33:00'),
	(150, 'I just got a dot so I could link it to my Apple Music only to find that I can’t. THATS ALL OF MY MUSIC THROWN OUT THE WINDOW! That was basically the entire reason I got this and I will have to pay to hear music I ALREADY OWN! What makes this problem worse is that the app is a legitimate maze, people! I want to do the simplest task with the app, and I spend at least DOUBLE the time I would actually need if the app was set up in an understandable way. No, TRIPLE THE TIME BECAUSE I HAVE TO SIT HERE AND WRITE THIS REVIEW SO PROGRAMMERS CAN FIX THIS AND BUYERS WILL DOWNLOAD WITH CAUTION!', 'Anonymous0214', 'iTunes', 2, 'Is it worth it?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 23:14:48'),
	(151, 'After the update on 21 Dec 2017, there are no options for Pandora or iHeart radio. Instead, Alexa tells me that they are not available in my region which is US.', 'Lil Rukia', 'iTunes', 1, 'No more Pandora or iHeart', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 00:23:46'),
	(152, 'Fun game. She even finds you an opponent. Merry christmas', 'Lifting Linda', 'iTunes', 5, 'Christmas music quiz', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 04:10:36'),
	(153, 'When I ask to play mediation it says \nOkay it will start \nAnd will last 6 minutes and then nothin', 'melody joyy', 'iTunes', 3, 'It speaks but won’t do what I tell it to do', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 07:21:39'),
	(154, 'Cannot ser up Alexa. It just doesn’t work.', 'Andres Scharifker', 'iTunes', 1, 'Doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 12:33:11'),
	(155, 'Doesn’t work with TPlink HS100 device that the Echo shipped with as a package.  Even after multiple reinstalls and factory resets, the free smart home plug that came as a as a promoter companion item is incomparable and broken. The app just keeps saying “discovery failed”. \n\nI’m not sure if people at amazon read these, but if you do: I’m returning both items and never buying amazon hardware again. Shell out a couple $$ to make an iOS app made — don’t subject your customers to your garbage software.', 'nester3056', 'iTunes', 1, 'Wow is this a bad app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 13:12:02'),
	(156, 'Since a few updates ago the app badgers you for your contact list.   I said no.  I meant no, but it relentlessly asks.   I was a strong proponent of Alexa and the app up until this point, but amazon is now being disrespectful to its customers.   Stop the nag, there are other options.  Ask once then let it go.   All I want is for the last screen I was in to be persistent when I open the app.   For me it’s smart home. Pretty simple and very codeable.   You get a new review when you fix this disrespect.', 'Man from Mass', 'iTunes', 1, 'Wants your personal contacts always', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 14:03:21'),
	(157, 'If I’d have know how awful this is, I’d have never bought an Echo. Also, let me say, I usually never take the time to review things, but if I can warn anyone away from this disaster, then good! The response time in the app is slow. It’s difficult to navigate. It won’t let me do things like train Alexa my voice or create a new list. All of this has been a bunch of useless garbage.', 'Trtlgrl44', 'iTunes', 1, 'Useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 15:59:41'),
	(158, 'if you know how to work the app it’s really helpful to figure out new things to ask Alexa! ( Try “Alexa, play song quiz” )', 'supergreatgameahdksm', 'iTunes', 5, 'Really helpful!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 16:22:21');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(159, 'Music unlimited needs major improvement in the Alexa app. Most of the time I can’t get music unlimited to load, but all the other music like Pandora load quickly. The actual music unlimited app works fine, too. This new update is terrible. The volume slider is too glitchy and can’t see the volume number because it’s directly under my finger. The developers need to read the reviews and fix this app. I’ve sent them feedback, received an email back, but nothing has been fixed.', 'Kweeda', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 16:47:39'),
	(160, 'I SIGN INTO MY AMAZON ACCOUNT AND THIS APP CRASHS I CANT USE MY ECHO DOT IF IT CRASHES PLEASE FIX IT. I WOULD BE HAPPY.TO GIVE IT 5 stars once it is fixed', 'Oshsiwnwwiqjwnwws', 'iTunes', 1, '5 STARS SO IT SHOWS UP ON TOP', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-23 23:47:28'),
	(161, 'Can’t believe this is the best selling voice assistant in the market with an ridiculous app. Getting the device to connect to internet takes forever, I have spent 2 hrs trying still not successful. Not because I don’t know how to do but the app is so irresponsive. Hope amazon is taking this seriously.', 'Manjitstr', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worst app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 00:25:03'),
	(162, 'After reinstalling the app i can\'t sign in.\nAnd how do i change the region language?', 'Ciaruscuro', 'iTunes', 1, 'Cant Sign in', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 02:13:36'),
	(163, 'App is becoming less and less relevant/buggy. Updates seem to revert backwards. When is the app going to be updated for iPhone X?!', 'Timmy Payne', 'iTunes', 1, 'QC', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 02:33:47'),
	(164, 'This app is the complete opposite of what you expect of Amazon\'s quality. App crashes and doesnt even load half the time. App is so terrible I can\'t even set an alarm on there.', 'BbbbbbVBbaaa', 'iTunes', 1, 'App is terrible', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 08:42:31'),
	(165, 'Almost once a week this app freezes on me when it asks if I want to allow Alexa to have access to my contacts. I click allow and nothing happens. I close app down and re-open and it comes back to same screen and nothing. It won’t let me push block or allow access to my contacts. I have completely shut my phone down and still doesn’t work. I have has to now three times delete the app from my phone and re-install to get the app to work. What a pain! This has now happened to my husband just today and he has had to do the same thing.  I hope this glitch gets fixed soon because it’s no use to me if I cant access the shopping list when I am at the store.', 'Mel4OSU', 'iTunes', 2, 'App freezes up almost weekly', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 12:46:46'),
	(166, 'This app is confusing, horribly designed, and glitchy. It also lacks a ton of user features that normal apps. Plus, when you have any questions it always just returns you back to the same pages. Plus, despite choosing and connecting to MY Pandora account, my Alexa always generates new, random, non-specific stations that are usually only partially related to my request. For example, I asked yesterday for my Pandora Christmas Jazz station and it could only make either a pure jazz station or Christmas carols, despite Pandora having a specific "Christmas Jazz" station. I love Amazon as a company and was very excited to get my Alexa, but I am very disappointed.', 'Guitarlover221', 'iTunes', 1, 'Disappointing and Poor Quality', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 12:56:07'),
	(167, 'Requires login even when network access not available.  Extremely extremely extremely slow, can take minutes to migrate from screen to screen.', 'LQQK_Here', 'iTunes', 1, 'Shopping List Pain', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 12:57:54'),
	(168, 'Can’t even get the app to load it’s stuck on the set up screen no matter what I do. Had an Android now I have iOS seems it has to be the iOS app. Really starting to hate amazon and there crap!', 'Dankstalivin', 'iTunes', 1, 'Startup', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 14:08:09'),
	(169, 'Stopped installing almost near the end. Unable to use the app.', 'Inuoa', 'iTunes', 1, 'Unable to install', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 15:07:59'),
	(170, 'I don’t want to upload my contacts to Amazon yet every time I open the App it’s forcing me to sign up.  There is no way to exit this permission screen to get to the home screen.  Dishonest practices.', 'Vacazion', 'iTunes', 1, 'Don’t want Alexa Call.. so I can’t use App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 17:32:23');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(171, 'Very glitchy, very confusing, very unintuitive to the point where I almost wish I never bought an echo. It can take 10 minutes just to find a simple feature, other features that I want to use are so confusing I can not find them anywhere in the app. Also very dumb that I have to call customer support in order to unlink my phone number from a different echo.', 'Bimet42', 'iTunes', 1, 'Horrible', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 19:01:05'),
	(172, 'Poor reliability, buggy, hectic app. Visually unappealing. This app needs a major overhaul. Does amazon even have a professional app developer on staff? This app makes me wonder.', 'skiaddict', 'iTunes', 1, 'Abysmal app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 20:39:06'),
	(173, 'Adding and removing smart devices is really the only thing I use this app for and it’s slow and awkward to use. It would also help if it supported the iPhone X.', 'MrCmonster', 'iTunes', 3, 'Needs work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 21:01:05'),
	(174, 'Also, the UX w the overstuffed hamburger menu is awful.', 'awolowiecki720', 'iTunes', 2, 'Still no iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 21:33:33'),
	(175, 'No, I don\'t like this app at all', 'Axmiami', 'iTunes', 2, 'Alexa', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-24 21:36:46'),
	(176, 'Amazon Apps come up as ‘App Support Unavailable’', 'AcroAlex', 'iTunes', 2, 'Can’t do much', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 01:03:22'),
	(177, 'Nice', 'Jjjjjjjjdjsjjdjdkd', 'iTunes', 5, 'Nice', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 02:17:56'),
	(178, 'After the app failed to do anything I un installed and tried to re install. Now it won’t install but it says done. I have shut off my phone and restarted it. Nothing is working', '78467204639', 'iTunes', 1, 'Doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 03:38:33'),
	(179, 'The app is extremely slow, and not optimized in it layout at all. Such a shame because the echo device itself is amazing. Also, 3 months now and still no iPhone X support?', 'Spacemoon56', 'iTunes', 1, 'Slow and Not optimized', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 06:07:01'),
	(180, 'This app is so helpful to beginner users for Alexa', 'Summer Emilyon', 'iTunes', 5, 'Good rate❤️❤️❤️', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 07:09:00'),
	(181, 'Christmas morning... 5 new devices and not one able to be set up because the app keeps cycling through the same 3 screens during set up. Keeps locking up and then resetting itself. I will be returning all of these devices the moment the store reopens.', 'Drunky Munky', 'iTunes', 1, 'Great idea, poor execution', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 13:07:56'),
	(182, 'This app is making my echo un-usable. It’s trash. Step up your game amazon. You’re loaded. Make some quality product.', 'skullmo', 'iTunes', 1, 'Garbage app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 13:32:58'),
	(183, 'This app is ridiculous. It literally took me 3 hours to get the foolish thing to function well enough for Alexa to learn my voice. I’m pretty close to ready to return the whole systems based on how bad this app is. Keep that in mind before ordering any of the Amazon devices.', 'Zoo713', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worst setup app ever', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 14:30:27'),
	(184, 'This is the worst app ever....', 'AG🐾', 'iTunes', 1, 'Awful', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 14:51:43'),
	(185, 'This is by far the slowest app I’ve encountered.  Makes me think twice about purchasing the echo.  Very painful.', 'Crissaaaaapp', 'iTunes', 2, 'Slow and laggy', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 15:08:21'),
	(186, 'This is quite possibly, as the title says, the worst app for iPhone I have ever used. To start, it takes about 10 tried for it to even connect to your device (I’m using the echo). Once you do manage to do that, it’s next to impossible to create a voice profile because the app won’t progress itself when you hit the next button unless you close out of the app and reopen it, get lucky and you’ll be at step 2/10. Can’t make it past there. It’s been about 10 minutes since I started, and literally just now, while typing this, my echo said “Your echo has received an update and will be available to use shortly.” I haven’t even gotten the thing setup and the device is already shutting itself down. Would not recommend the device or iPhone app to a single person, not even my greatest enemy.', 'Hawkyfan', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worst app I’ve ever used', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 15:26:01');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(187, 'I really wasn\'t too upset with the app, but it certainly wasn\'t what I\'d call "good." The whole app was unwieldy, but admittedly better than one star. It got one star because I\'m hoping a continuous stream of bad reviews will spur the developers to fix it. They don\'t seem to have taken any pride in their work with this one, sadly.', 'Jordan Kozuszek', 'iTunes', 1, 'Meh...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 16:01:25'),
	(188, 'I got and amazon echo for Xmas, and the thing is nothing like the commercials. It does nothing, it can’t even play music. I’ve tried connecting it to Spotify, but it never connects. Worst app and worst product.', 'xX_Hella_Sw4ggy_Xx', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 16:23:02'),
	(189, 'This app is horrible. Got an echo for xmas and can’t use it. First couldn’t download the app. Now that the app has finally downloaded after 10 attempts, I can’t get a txt sent to my phone to register the dot. Likely going to return the echo due to the app not working', 'xmarkmanningx', 'iTunes', 1, 'POS', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 16:25:52'),
	(190, 'This app is amazing I downloaded it today I have a iPhone 6s it works perfect', 'love remind', 'iTunes', 5, 'Awesome sauce', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 17:18:18'),
	(191, 'I received an amazon Alexa from my loving wife and at first we were excited and hopeful. The problem started when the instructions said to down load this app.... as it stands I am unable to use this and will probably be returning it to amazon because of the poor quality app that is unable to get through the verification process with out error.', 'Betchface', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worst Christmas present this year', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 17:34:01'),
	(192, 'I just got the amazon echo, and it is just so immensely hard to connect to. I have spent over 30 minutes trying to connect to it, and I\'ve done everything I can to fix it. It just absolutely refuses to cooperate. I could swear that they make it impossible to setup. I very much despise this app, and the way it is organized is revolting. I can\'t believe it and I would rate it below one star if it was physically possible. It might be the most infuriating app I have ever used, and being an iPhone user for over 5 years that is not something easy to do (excuse my grammatical mistakes I just feel typing this is the only way to get my anger out).\n\nPS. I have still not gotten it to work', 'Isgsga', 'iTunes', 1, 'Connecting to the echo is insufferable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 17:39:05'),
	(193, 'Buggy!', 'denkst', 'iTunes', 1, 'Ugh!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 17:51:18'),
	(194, 'App is slow and doesn’t function. Echo is useless', 'Cammmmeroon', 'iTunes', 1, 'Pretty useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 17:55:31'),
	(195, 'For some reason when I enter my phone number it takes twenty minutes to send a code and then once it sends, wont verify', 'Thepandanerd27', 'iTunes', 3, 'Won’t Verify My Phone Number', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 18:03:53'),
	(196, 'With iPhone 7plus and airport router', 'Mbrei', 'iTunes', 1, 'Setup doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 18:16:13'),
	(197, 'I have Prime, tried to set up the account on Christmas Day.  They sent me a code to my phone that took 20 minutes to receive.  I entered the code over and over and I got an ‘invalid code’ message over and over.  Asked for another code...20 minutes later got it...’invalid’ over and over.  Gave up...smashed it with a hammer and then lit it on fire.', 'Freeholdnjusa', 'iTunes', 1, 'Failed me for Christmas', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 18:26:11'),
	(198, 'It is AWFUL and takes sometimes even WEEKS to connect to your device. My kids got it at Christmas and it didn’t connect until late February', 'lit113', 'iTunes', 1, 'HORRIBLE APP', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 18:50:33'),
	(199, 'I just got my Alexa echo.today tried downloading the Alexa app and it’s taking an hour and a half to download super slow and I have a high-speed connection and I know our internets not slow. They need to update the app to where it’s not slow. This is stupid. I love the Alexa it’s just taking a long time to download. Not My Internet speed', 'allenjoshua839', 'iTunes', 4, 'Slow app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 18:53:22');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(200, 'This app is garbage. Unfortunately you need it to set up an Alexa device. You would think a company like Amazon would be able to have a proper app developed but I guess not.', 'Biohazardshrimp', 'iTunes', 1, 'Love our Echo’s but hate this app!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 19:26:40'),
	(201, 'I got the app today and as soon as I was able to hook up my echo dot every time I opened the app it would crash and take me back to my home screen. I deleted the app and downloaded it again but it still isn’t working. How am I supposed to keep it from crashing? Any tips? Amazon needs to fix this.', 'Gracie2603', 'iTunes', 1, 'Crashes a lot', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 19:41:22'),
	(202, 'I had problem with Alexa recognizing multiple devices. After disabling it would recognize again. Finally realized you had to disable duplicate and DRAG TO TRASH IN UPPER RIGHT in skills. PERMANENTLY eliminated duplicates and Alexa again recognized single listing.  Hope this helps somebody', 'Donald2013', 'iTunes', 5, 'Alexa recognizing disabled devices twice', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 19:51:21'),
	(203, 'This app is driving me to drink. I love my Echo and Dots and Alexa is powerful and i love to see the skills continue to develop, but this app is simply awful and needs to be completely re-worked from the ground up. At least the Smart Home section. It continually drops connections and adds old ones randomly without going through discovery. I used to have TP-Link smart plugs but I\'ve since replaces the ones that controlled lights to HUE. Ive disabled and deleted these plugs, but they constantly come back. They will have the same name as the HUE lights so it gets confused. It will work fine then randomly it will say the HUE device isn\'t responding, but it works fine if I go into the Phillips app or any of the other third party HUE apps to turn them on or off. \n\nThe latest patch added the ability to delete devices, but they still come back and it throws Alexa for a loop when three devices, two of which don\'t exist, are named living room. \n\nPlease, Amazon, you are an excellent company and Alexa is clearly the future, don\'t let google pass you by because your app that controls her is garbage.', 'c-b-w', 'iTunes', 2, 'Ugh! Frustrating!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 20:04:19'),
	(204, 'It’s pretty easy to use. It needs iPhone X support. Could use a touch of Love appearance wise. Once you figure it out it’s easy.', 'Allen Flupper', 'iTunes', 4, 'Easy but could be better.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 20:33:45'),
	(205, 'The app always crashes and won’t let me give permission so I have to delete and redownload.', 'Swanald713', 'iTunes', 1, 'Crash', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 21:10:09'),
	(206, 'The app, from what I could see, was fine... though many flaws including not being able to select certain commands(like wake words) and other issues.\n\nBut, then I logged out. What happened next makes no sense, and shouldn’t happen; I CAN’T LOG IN!!\nI have entered my password correctly, multiple times. When that didn’t work, I changed it (seven times) to no avail. Until this issue that shouldn’t happen is fixed, I can’t say anything nice to these developers.', 'Zanderaptor', 'iTunes', 1, 'Good for the ten minutes of access I had', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 21:28:04'),
	(207, 'Can’t link Apple Music and you can only link contacts that signed up for amazon messaging. Only good if you have another music service or just want for asking random questions', 'AverySKking', 'iTunes', 1, 'Bad Christmas gift for sure', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 22:16:57'),
	(208, 'Love it. Just got one for Xmas. Please add support for Apple Music.', 'Me90876', 'iTunes', 4, 'So far so good', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 23:35:37'),
	(209, 'it’s really a pain that you can’t use alexa with apple music, ruins the whole experience', 'E12r34i56c78', 'iTunes', 1, 'PLEASE ADD APPLE MUSIC', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-25 23:55:03'),
	(210, 'Catch up with the rest of the industry and add iPhone X support to get your stars back', 'Benmattson', 'iTunes', 1, 'Needs iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 00:29:07'),
	(211, 'Bugs are mainly gone and its getting better every update..', 'Ourdoc', 'iTunes', 5, 'Great app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 01:13:53');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(212, 'I want to like this app. But the awkwardness of the volume control alone is enough to drive someone crazy. \n\nAlexa gets better each day, I hope this app can too.', 'Uncle Buck Hunter', 'iTunes', 2, 'Please FIX VOLUME CONTROL!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!1', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 01:56:29'),
	(213, 'I like that it is very easy to navigate through the app but I would like to be able to tell my Alexa to do things through the app; like set an alarm from the app.', 'Packer5221', 'iTunes', 3, 'Eh...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 02:36:52'),
	(214, 'App doesn’t work at all', 'Z_31', 'iTunes', 1, '1 star', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 03:10:18'),
	(215, 'This app has always been a little hard to maneuver through... but the benefits of Alexa make it worthwhile.\nMy husband and I just updated phones, updated the app and hoped to use the cool calling features .... contact list won’t load nor will our profiles at top. Same on both phones!  \nPlease fix!!!!!  Worked great on our old iPhone 6’s', 'trying out new tech', 'iTunes', 2, 'Yikes!!! No contacts on my phone with update!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 03:11:03'),
	(216, 'My gosh it’s so slow!!!', 'Mister Stephens', 'iTunes', 1, 'Sooooo slooooow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 03:58:38'),
	(217, 'I wish I could rate zero stars. Amazon should be embarrassed by this pile of crap app. Why should I be forced to default to conversations? Who cares? Why should you need my contacts? Get off me and be a convenience.', 'Slimwork', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worst app ever', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 04:00:53'),
	(218, 'I can’t edit my Echo device name or add/change the location address in Settings.  When I select the edit option, the edit screen appears for a couple seconds, then closes before I can type anything.', 'Alp-max', 'iTunes', 1, 'Buggy app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 05:01:53'),
	(219, 'I want to listen to music on my echo dot but I can’t because I don’t have any of the listed music apps but I have Apple Music, so could Apple Music be added to the list of music options?', 'Yazzie b', 'iTunes', 3, 'Different music options', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 05:01:36'),
	(220, 'Really slow and glitchy :(', 'problyeating', 'iTunes', 1, ':(', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 05:59:25'),
	(221, 'Alexa is disconnecting from amazon music unlimited every time when I wanna Play a song , so I have to sign up every time on amazon music when I want to hear my music', 'Edu1286', 'iTunes', 1, 'Error with amazon music', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 06:09:28'),
	(222, 'Excellent but we need iPhone X support', 'SAOK83', 'iTunes', 5, 'Great', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 11:17:03'),
	(223, 'I agree that the Alexa app gets worse and worse. Now there appears to be no way to drop in on your Alexa devices from the app. Why take away features?', 'Andy C in DC', 'iTunes', 1, 'Drop in no longer available on app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 12:32:25'),
	(224, 'This app makes no sense at all it is just completely junk, I can’t even sync up my Spotify account! And lightbulbs won’t work either so if you have flux or Smart life it won’t work. This makes me so mad because I spend MONEY for your products amazon so shut up get on with your life and PVC my fat butt', 'PRO38MLG', 'iTunes', 1, 'TERRIBLE', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 13:39:42'),
	(225, 'Alexa ap very confusing, very slow on my iPhone 5s and app eats my battery to nothing!!\n\nI can’t believe Amazon sends out such a poorly written app for their Echo products', 'K6sdw', 'iTunes', 1, 'Horrible app!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 15:04:51'),
	(226, 'I want to send messages, I look on the Alexa App for the conversations tab, none.  Please update the app to have the conversations tab on all platforms.  Very disappointed.', 'Kitty Kat 2.0', 'iTunes', 1, 'Very disappointed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 15:40:20'),
	(227, 'All music is subscription based. Google has free music on shuffle. Clarity and speaker quality isn\'t comparable to their competition. Returning this and buying a Google Home. Junk compared to what else is out there!', 'Going to buy a Google Home', 'iTunes', 2, 'Going to buy a Google Home', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 15:53:46'),
	(228, 'Sometimes the app will show the songs playing on the station I’ve chosen so that I can give them a thumbs up or thumbs down but more often than not, that screen won’t load.', 'Zoemax1', 'iTunes', 1, 'Frustrating', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 16:00:04');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(229, 'Setting up is pretty straight forward. \nOne issue I do see with Alexa, it can not tell me my radio stations in Pandora. If this is can be resolved, I will be very appreciative. Alexa i a great piece of technology!!!!', 'Golf4dee', 'iTunes', 5, 'Ask ALEXA', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 16:05:06'),
	(230, 'As I am aware that Apple is not owned by amazon, it’s a fact that Apple Music is hands down the best music app in the world. It’s just a suggestion that The Amazon Echo plays Apple Music, to make an already great app even better. Something as simple as that will bring my rating up 1 1/2 stars. The other 1/2 will be granted once Alexa starts answering more of my questions', 'Yamssss', 'iTunes', 3, 'No Apple Music', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 17:12:29'),
	(231, 'This is my first foray into the echo arena and I mush say getting the echo setup using this app was very difficult and took an absurd amount of random searching, tapping, password resetting and ultimately a sh*t load of patience before the app finally decided to be merciful and start working.  This device was a xmas gift and once setup, is a pretty cool device.  The sound is amazing for its size.  It plays music clearly with a surprising amount of bass.  If the developers take a page from Apple and make the setup of the app intuitive and goof proof, the sky is the limit for the success of these devices and integration into homes and offices.  The echo platform has a lot of potential, but the Alexa app is its Achilles heel.', 'Breeze214', 'iTunes', 1, 'Painful Setup', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 17:23:04'),
	(232, 'Can’t get past the setup page. The buttons don’t respond. Terrible app.', 'A1990All', 'iTunes', 1, 'Waste of time', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 18:20:56'),
	(233, 'Setup is impossible and I\'m very comfortable with electronics. All it says is go to your Alexa app. No help at all. This piece of garbage is getting returned!', 'Dan353z', 'iTunes', 1, 'Doesn\'t work, no support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 20:14:25'),
	(234, 'C’mon you guys. I’ve reset everything. Deleted everything. Reloaded everything. Apps deleted and reloaded. Et cetera. Et cetera. Et cetera. Groups no longer work. WeMo does not connect easily. It’s not a WeMo problem, it’s Alexa.', 'Crrritic', 'iTunes', 1, 'Doesn’t work with “Groups” anymore', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 23:02:48'),
	(235, 'I update my Dot and now it takes twice as long to respond and sometimes it freezes up it’s not working your update. Your update need to update', 'Mouse8153', 'iTunes', 1, 'Your update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-26 23:02:37'),
	(236, 'This app is annoying and needs major improvements. I understand that the Alexa devices are popular and with the increased use there will be issue, however, the app is slow, buggy, sporadic on when it decides to work and would not pull up all the options that the app said would work with my device.', 'TXJ1970', 'iTunes', 2, 'Disappointment', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 00:01:16'),
	(237, 'I am trying to set up my amazon echo dot with this app and it refuses to do so and keeps bringing me back to the sign in page. I am positive this is the right password and email yet it continues to fail. TERRIBLE APP!!!', 'Anomompus', 'iTunes', 1, 'TERRIBLE', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 03:05:48'),
	(238, 'why does amazon hate apple???', 'LeHausdeGaGa', 'iTunes', 1, 'this app is so bad', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 06:20:46'),
	(239, 'Other reviewers are correct this is getting WORSE.  it used to function correctly eight out of 10 times.  Now it is more like seven out of 10 times.  When it fails it fails big and will repeat the same mistake ad infinitum.  Requesting A classic hit often results in the playing of an off brand live version that no one has heard of or wants to hear.  Why antagonize the consumer like this.  ANSWER: Greed!   The actual development of this product has been dropped in the consumers lap. It is not so much a failure of the product as it is a failure of the new tech business model.  If all you want to do is set timers and Stream radio stations via voice command then this is your gadget.  But even then with all the spying and privacy concerns I would not recommend it.', 'Erodox', 'iTunes', 1, 'Frustration factor renders it worthless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 13:18:07');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(240, 'Cmon Amazoooon. I need to use echo dot in Brazil but it is impossible! Weather doesn’t work because it set to US and it’s impossible to change. Spotify doesn’t work because its set to work ONLY in some veeery few countries. We have Amazon Brazil but your Alexa echo system is useless here! MAKE IT WORLDWIDE LIKE GOOGLE HOME PLEAAASSSEEEE', 'TaisFM', 'iTunes', 1, 'Needs to work better outside US!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 14:34:32'),
	(241, 'I was expecting the bugs to be fixed by the latest update, but they just got worse. It now refuses to open the Lists screen and a couple others. Please hire some decent iOS programmers to fix it. App works fine on PC and Android.', 'Wizard7', 'iTunes', 1, 'App getting worse with each update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 15:21:36'),
	(242, 'This app takes forever for menus to load. Also finding some things like adjusting your flash briefing are hard to find.', 'Jpcollins909', 'iTunes', 2, 'Terribly Slow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 15:33:07'),
	(243, 'To start off, i have tried to set up my echo for about 5 times already, and it just brings me back to, “Your echo isn’t connected to a wifi network.”\nMy wifi is working perfectly fine and I connected to the Amazon wifi on my phone. It continues not to work, showing the orange line over and over. Then when I try to go into the app to get help, the wifi is off because I am connected to the echo instead of the normal wifi. This is a nightmare to set up.', 'ThatOneRandomCatLady', 'iTunes', 2, 'So Hard to Set up', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 16:16:04'),
	(244, 'Since the last update, it is stuck on the setup page where it asks if I want to allow it to use my contacts... doesn’t matter what I hit but won’t move past that! Very frustrating when I use the app for my shopping list and can’t view it when I need it!!', 'Opiet11', 'iTunes', 1, 'Something wrong', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 17:57:22'),
	(245, 'Please update the app for the iPhone X. So we can take advantage of the full screen!', 'arturosjr', 'iTunes', 2, 'iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 21:03:41'),
	(246, 'Come on...', 'Amp45', 'iTunes', 3, 'iPhone X UI', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 21:21:55'),
	(247, 'LOVE IT #alexa', 'Abby da awesome', 'iTunes', 5, 'Love it', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 22:40:13'),
	(248, 'Application needs improvements because it is not user-friendly.\n\nThe app is slow to recognize wifi sync, slow to recognize speaker on the smart phone (iPhone) listed in settings.\n\nThe hardware (Amazon Alexa) is impeded because the poor\nSoftware interface currently available.', 'S.Miles', 'iTunes', 2, 'Alexa application needs improvements', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 22:42:19'),
	(249, 'We just purchased amazon echo show and are very disappointed the device has a camera speakerphone and screen. However, it is not equipped with a security feature. This device would be great if it also worked as an IP camera where we can set alarms and get notifications in case of emergencies so proper measures can be taken', 'Giusse718', 'iTunes', 1, 'Security', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 23:23:58'),
	(250, 'I just set up Alexa today and am baffled at how low-tech it is. Setup was also not user friendly. I’ll post an update after use, but will likely return it. I’m also finding it impossible to change my phone number on the app.', 'Hawaii lovin', 'iTunes', 2, 'Convoluted and low-tech', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-27 23:42:00'),
	(251, 'Alexa is clearly not ready to grasp the finer points of Hue control.  Limited color selections and a clunky interface make using the app annoying.  I plan to buy a Phillips bridge instead.  I hope Amazon realizes they have to develop worthwhile software to control their hardware if they want to keep the Echo Plus in use.', 'BigSwingFace', 'iTunes', 1, 'Hue lighting nearly useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 00:26:58');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(252, 'I love the echo and the dot and they always have the answers I ask them. But lately my app is not working. Once I open the app, It will ask me to allow permissions for Alexa and I click allow but nothing happens. I then have to delete the app and then download the app again. But then it works completely fine until I close the app. Then the whole process starts again. It’s also affecting my alarms I’m assuming because I have not heard my alarm go off in quite some time. I can only guess it’s because of the permissions. But other than that, I absolutely love these Amazon products and hope to buy more soon. Just fix the app.', 'Meggymeg95', 'iTunes', 3, 'Bittersweet', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 01:13:01'),
	(253, 'Developer needs to get up with the game here. The app is not user friendly, doesn’t let you delete your history in one shot, it has to be done individually and that is annoying as the app forces you to answer questions before you delete?', 'Carmengarcia1975', 'iTunes', 2, 'You could do better...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 02:02:11'),
	(254, 'It would be great if you could ask Alexa to play music for a certain amount of time\n(Play music for the next 30 minutes) so people could fall asleep listening to music. \n\nAlso, there should be an ability to change the music song/station you wake up to in the morning, and you should be able to have multiple alarms.\n\nOther than that, I think Alexa is great, and I love using her. These improvements would be amazing!!', 'Caitie121', 'iTunes', 4, 'Music and Alarm System', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 05:22:41'),
	(255, 'Es lenta, mal UX, no sirve la sincronizacion con iDevices', 'rarias84', 'iTunes', 1, 'No me gusta', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 09:45:28'),
	(256, 'My biggest gripe is the in app volume. The dial is on the far right and to slide it with my hands completely covers itself so i can’t read the number. Makes changing the volume in app worthless. Move it to the bottom or display the number more effectively, or give a +/- option', 'twhp17', 'iTunes', 3, 'Volume', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 12:22:58'),
	(257, 'I was playing a song and askedfor the album name just to see what came back, she listed song name and artist, then continued. It was “illusion sky” by hallas (that first “a” actually has an umlaut), and the album was “excerpts from a future past”. So i tried asking her to play that album, she named it perfectly, but told me she couldnt find it, even though we were playing a song from it. I even tried finding “supernaut” by black sabbath, she names the song perfectly, yet magically still cannot find it. Edit: found out spotify lists the song as “supernaut: remastered”. Doesnt recognize comments like “alexa, thats a good one, but next”. Come on guys, same old a.i. Just With a more lucrative utilization, thats what i expected. Gmme something i dont expect, and ill pay you like a tax.', 'Caelumerrare', 'iTunes', 2, 'Spotify album seeking needs work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 13:05:06'),
	(258, 'Turning on off your iPhone disconnects the music. Typing turns off the music. Etc. \nthis doesn’t happen on my pixel xl2....', 'Always Improving...', 'iTunes', 2, 'It’s not there yet...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 13:08:56'),
	(259, 'The app continually is asking for permissions but then I can’t get past that page. I have to uninstall and re install the app to get it to work but then next time I open it it does it again. I love telling Alexa what I need from the store so I don’t have to search for a pen each time but then I can never get into the app to see my list.', 'Kjbar1375695', 'iTunes', 1, 'Can’t access anything', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 13:31:19'),
	(260, 'I am giving up trying to set up the Dot using this app. Between many attempts, using different devices and both setting up a new account or using the old account, which logs into Amazon just fine, and trying both 2.4 and 5ghz networks, I could not connect to the network.  I can see why they would lower the price for Dot so low!\n\nSome of the attempts took upwards of 30 seconds for a key to be entered into the app from when the key was pressed.  Other attempts simply resulted in a blank screen.  Overall whoever wrote this app should be embarrassed and also fired.', 'Joe another name', 'iTunes', 1, 'Piece of trash', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 17:18:12');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(261, 'I never write reviews but with an app this terrible. It was much needed. It has taken me 4+ hours to sync my Echo and it still won’t work. The app is glitchy and takes 3-15 minutes to get to the next part of the setup. I still have not setup my Echo and it has taken at least 4 tries so far.', 'It\'s ur mama', 'iTunes', 1, 'Update ASAP', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 17:27:15'),
	(262, 'I love using Echo! However, it should have a way to block explicit music. You can easily set parental controls for Amazon TV & Movies. Why not for music? I would change my rating if we could filter the music.', 'A K Teacher', 'iTunes', 1, 'Filter needed!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 18:28:53'),
	(263, '“Discovery Failed” when trying to add any devices, such as my Nest Cams. Alexa isn’t even available as it says “playback control not supported”.  So what is the point of this app then?!', 'SK2_2', 'iTunes', 1, 'If it worked maybe I’d like it.…', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 18:31:29'),
	(264, 'That you have to use this app to manage your Alexa and dot setup is beyond frustrating and cumbersome. Amazon has dropped the ball here. Can’t easily connect to amazon music unlimited, can’t do the simplest things without a dozen clicks in navigation, and defaulting to a screen I could care less about instead of opening on a screen I want to see is plain dumb. Jeff Bezos should be ashamed.', 'wunten', 'iTunes', 1, 'What a buggy piece of garbage', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-28 21:26:46'),
	(265, 'When I go to open the app it just say on the same page. Buttons don’t work. Had to reinstall twice now!', 'Jadetec', 'iTunes', 2, 'Keep locking up', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 01:09:00'),
	(266, 'Everything about this app is a joke. It’s slow, and if/when you get to the area you want it crashes. I have the iPhone 6 and most updated software. (12-23-17). I have reset my phone and tried to be on the app, but of course it continues to crash. I honest can’t believe amazon is getting away with this. They sold thousands of echos this year and this is how they want consumers to interact with the devices?! I want answers!!! We consumers pay for product we expect it to work!!! I’m going to guess this app is still a year out before it’s working correctly. DON’T BUY AMAZON STUFF JUST YET!!\n\nEDIT NOTE: (12-29-2017) spoke with an amazon rep and all they can say is that they know it’s not working properly. That’s it!? So yea I guess I can’t link my Phillips hue bulbs or set up my other echos I paid for. Thinking about selling the whole setup for cheap because of the awful app and customer service. I will also be telling everyone I know NOT to get this product.', 'MasonMik81', 'iTunes', 1, 'Still crashes and is slow after iOS 11.2.1', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 02:45:48'),
	(267, 'I like it BUT I cannot access YouTube. Apparently amazon and google are feuding. So that’s my problem ha ha. I bought it for Christmas for me when YouTube was available and now it’s not when I am able to use it. Huh. Also allrecipes is very glitchy. Alexa brings up my recipe and then if I don’t touch the screen she goes back to the home screen and I don’t know how to get her back to the recipe without staring all over. My phone was better for that. But I wanted the echo for this. Everything else so far is ok. But I haven’t evolved all her skills yet. Just disappointed about YouTube. Hopefully amazon starts selling google stuff again so their customers that have the echo are happy again. And fix allrecipes!!', 'Kristyven', 'iTunes', 3, 'Was very excited but now I’m not sure', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 03:19:15'),
	(268, 'Spent over three hours trying to set up, what about portless piece of equipment. Would not recommend, absolute waste of time.', 'Joel Uran', 'iTunes', 1, 'Disappointed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 03:35:46'),
	(269, 'Echo, and smart home are amazing. I am proud to report or use them both all the time. However, from the smart home section in this app, it would be great to show what lights are lit.  Than you don’t have to go into each one individually when you’re away from the house to find out which ones are on.', 'Pfermo', 'iTunes', 3, 'Smart Home', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 13:24:01');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(270, 'Alexa can do anything else BUT find any songs, stations, or genres from Prime Music. IT works well with Pandora though.', 'dcspace', 'iTunes', 2, 'Alexa Can’t Even Find Prime Music', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 13:53:06'),
	(271, 'This App needs some serious revamping.  Luv the Echo Show but the interface with the App needs some rethinking and revamping.', 'Glenart2k', 'iTunes', 1, 'Siri-iously revamping needed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 18:38:41'),
	(272, 'Shameful app. No time for Amazon\'s crappy app. Returning the Echo. Buying Google.', 'Mark My Word', 'iTunes', 1, 'Shameful', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-29 22:48:00'),
	(273, 'Love my Echoes but this app is subpar. The interface is unintuitive and the music is especially frustrating. I’ve spent more time fighting my Echoes to play simultaneously than I have listened to actual music. Alexa, for the last time, yes I want to stop the other stream so I can listen to music on both. No, I do not want you to then stop all music entirely and ignore my previous request.', 'AMC_37', 'iTunes', 2, 'Needs work...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 00:26:25'),
	(274, 'I have an Amazon prime account but it won’t let me use its benefits even though I’m signed into the Alexa app with the corresponding prime email address. There is no intuitive way to remedy this and I feel like I wasted my money.', 'Laughingwarlock', 'iTunes', 1, 'Useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 01:02:34'),
	(275, 'I’m constantly trying to set up my echo dot  but it can’t seem to connect to my WiFi.. .it keeps sayin “unable to connect at this time please try again” or sometimes it doesn’t proceed to the next step, after I’ve connected my phone to the echo dot. It was working fine until I’ve changed internet providers.', 'Masstah', 'iTunes', 1, 'Unable to connect to WiFi', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 04:15:56'),
	(276, 'Was working on older version. Signed out, now I\'m locked out of account - keeps saying timed out! Call Amazon Alexa customer service and was told to delete app and try again tomorrow. I might as well be told to build a time machine and go back in time when it worked! With so much push on Amazon devices, this App has crippled them!', 'toyzs22', 'iTunes', 1, 'Worst App ever developed! Useless!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 04:22:37'),
	(277, 'Using this app on my iPhone. Fabulous speech and voice capabilities. Wish Apple would let me replace Siri with Alexa. Wish Alexa could be integrated with my iPhone\'s microphone so I don\'t have to open the Amazon shopping app to access Alexa. Love how Alexa can read all my favorite news headline stories. Love all the new skills Alexa continues to acquire.', 'Elsa B.', 'iTunes', 4, 'Positive- my first encounter with the Alexa AI', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 12:44:48'),
	(278, 'Really not gripes about app features other than shopping list not easily accessible. My main gripe is the app isn’t formatted for iPhone X screen yet. I just picked up an Alexa an noticed this. Google home app has already been updated to support iPhone 10 screen size.', 'TxSurfer01', 'iTunes', 3, 'iPhone X Support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 12:45:34'),
	(279, 'Please fix. Can’t access anything in the app after this recent update!', 'TTOP71', 'iTunes', 1, 'App doesn’t work on iPad after update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 14:17:32'),
	(280, 'I used to love this app but right now I literally can’t use it. Every time I open the app it asks for me to give Amazon permissions with the options of “later” or “allow.” Well, the problem is no matter how many times I click “allow” nothing happens. So I try clicking “later” but the same thing happens-absolutely nothing. Because I can’t get past this page I am unable to use the app! I deleted the app which did work for about a week but now I’m back to having the permissions page come up every time I open it. Extremely frustrating. Amazon needs to focus on making their existing products work instead of trying to do anything and everything in the world. It’s better to have a few great products versus a ton of non working ones.', 'Cassdaw', 'iTunes', 2, 'Permissions page won’t let me use app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 16:06:30'),
	(281, 'At first, I wasn’t as thrilled with the app. However, with a little use and trial and error, I now enjoy the app very much.', 'RuthieG75', 'iTunes', 5, 'Improves as I learn', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 16:26:05');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(282, 'With the resources amazon allocated to Alexa why is this app such sh¡t?  Feels and functions like a web app from 2007. \n\nOne issue that drives me nuts is the lack of  synchronized state of the currently playing audio.', 'Peter Schussheim', 'iTunes', 1, 'Why is this so mediocre?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 16:31:33'),
	(283, 'Gave 1 star because 0 stars wasn’t an option...   The setup couldn’t be any less intuitive.  I am returning my echo because the setup is so difficult using this app.', 'JTW1833', 'iTunes', 1, 'Horrible app...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 19:01:09'),
	(284, 'Super laggy and full of glitches and is SO slow', 'gamer: FIREBOLT321', 'iTunes', 3, 'GARBAGE', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 20:52:34'),
	(285, 'Since using this update I can no longer access any of the Alexa skills, lists, etc. ... just get a blank screen. What is going on? Give me my skills, lists, etc. back!', 'Smedly Butler', 'iTunes', 1, 'Don’t update!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 20:52:14'),
	(286, 'You can create a smart device like the Echo but you can’t find a team to make an iPhone app functional? This app LAGS like none other. You have to delete scenes, devices etc one by one & its a 3-4 click process each time that also LAGS. \nGet your ish together Amazon.', 'tcafranz', 'iTunes', 1, 'Come on Amazon', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 21:08:29'),
	(287, 'This app is very slow, as though the company that makes it has no access to cloud servers. It’s bloated with amazon’s attempt to turn the Echo into some kind of social device. (Has anyone you met ever asked for your Echo contact info?) It can’t do basic things, like integrate its lists with iOS Reminders. The scenes and routines are very crude and cannot be edited in any efficient manner. So in practice I almost never use Alexa to manage any smart home devices. Most of the skills are half baked. This app makes great hardware it manages virtually useless. This app is the only reason my Echo is a $100 timer.', 'Vulgar demos', 'iTunes', 1, 'Pervasive problems', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 23:09:49'),
	(288, 'With a colossal amount of negative reviews vs. the number of butt kissing reviews, I am convinced the positive reviews are produced by reputation management software. \n\nThis app, as well as the device, can kiss where the sun doesn’t shine. I couldn’t even get it to connect to the WiFi, and I sure as hell am not wasting precious time “googling.”', 'missduranie', 'iTunes', 1, 'No.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 23:25:01'),
	(289, 'Errors when loading conversations review, no iPhone X support. Makes me concerned about shopping on Amazon when this is the state of their developers...', 'Shane-C', 'iTunes', 1, 'Buggy, No iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-30 23:49:41'),
	(290, 'Trying to get the app to work is a miracle based on how slow it is.', 'kris < 3', 'iTunes', 1, 'Slow as possible', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 00:01:57'),
	(291, 'No multi room setting available in settings where it should be so can’t link my devices!! The reason I got this crap in the first place!!', 'Dudeman06', 'iTunes', 1, 'No multi room available', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 00:46:10'),
	(292, 'the app crashes constantly. i can\'t even go to the settings tab without it freezing.', 'TheAwesomology', 'iTunes', 1, 'unusable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 00:56:22'),
	(293, 'It\'s been a couple months now since the iPhone X was released and during that time, there have been multiple updates to this app but there is STILL no iPhone X screen support! How hard could it be to add that? Amazon has 5,000 people on their Alexa team and they can\'t do it. I have apps installed that were made by one guy in his basement that have iPhone X support. This is seriously ridiculous.', 'Gary_OC', 'iTunes', 1, 'Still no iPhone X screen support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 01:07:53'),
	(294, 'The iPhone X has been out for how long now and the latest update as of 7 hours ago still doesn’t have iPhone X display support? Come on Amazon. The app is basic for functionality and navigation and seems more like a hassle to use than it should. Make it more streamline and easier to manage.', 'Bjaminkelley88', 'iTunes', 2, 'No iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 01:07:16'),
	(295, 'Still no optimization for the iPhone X????', 'roaddaw9', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 02:25:16');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(296, 'ARE YOU working on the crashing 12/30/2017? This crashing  _constantly_  has been going on way too long! I kept thinking you surely must be rolling it back to when it didn\'t crash, over & over again but I see no end to this! Takes \'forever\' to launch & then crashes over & over again!', 'Chuckeva', 'iTunes', 2, 'ARE YOU working on the crashing 12/30/2017', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 02:30:51'),
	(297, 'I love the amazon echo I just wish u could like actually talk to it like it can’t hold a conversation at all. If it could that would be great other than that I love my amazon echo and the app helps show me what I can do with it.', 'Madimay5232', 'iTunes', 4, 'Amazon echo', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 03:04:14'),
	(298, 'If it doesn’t work with HomeKit and Siri, I’m out!  Apple HomePod, here I come!!!', 'Tinkerbell4444', 'iTunes', 1, 'No Siri, No Deal', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 03:36:56'),
	(299, 'Es un poco confusa de usar, agregar o eliminar dispositivos inteligentes es un poco “tricky” y aún sigo esperando update para iPhone X. Sin contar el hecho que aún Alexa no habla español.', 'A. Càceres', 'iTunes', 2, 'Por mejorar', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 05:13:40'),
	(300, 'Did you seriously have the nerve to push an update w/o F**** iPhone X support?!?', 'Jayri54', 'iTunes', 1, 'Really ??', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 06:16:55'),
	(301, 'This app works very well for me but you guys must update the app to support the iPhone X!', 'Doolerds', 'iTunes', 3, 'iPhone X support!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 07:01:09'),
	(302, 'PLEASE add support for Alexa to play self created radio stations in Pandora and Spotify. I don’t want to hear playlists where I know what artists and songs are next. I use the radio feature of these apps to create stations from bands I like in which the app chooses similar bands and songs form different bands I may not know. It is a fantastic way to explore new music  it seems it would be easy to add “Alexa, play (station name)radio on Spotify” \nThis is one feature I truly miss', 'Hebbajebba', 'iTunes', 3, 'Spotify and pandora radio support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 14:08:05'),
	(303, 'Just one example for starters. I\'m trying to set up a voice profile. I\'m directed to Settings, Account, Your Voice. Under Account, there is no "Your Voice" option. Something so simple, so basic. What is this, 1990?', 'Pacfamily', 'iTunes', 1, 'The Alexa "Miracle" is this App\'s Level of Incompetence', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 14:31:06'),
	(304, 'They updated their shopping app... It\'s hard to consider Amazon a tech giant when they can\'t even update an app for iPhone X... I would use this app a lot more.', 'TheAceOfNames', 'iTunes', 2, 'No iPhone X support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 14:38:06'),
	(305, 'What did you even do to this app lately?! It used to be useable but recently everything you do in the app takes 10-20 seconds. Click a button? 10-20 seconds. Tap in the search bar to search for a skill? 10-20 seconds before I could type. I had to spend nearly 10 minutes to get through the screens to set up a new Echo. It is pretty much unusable at this point. How do you even make an app that slow?', 'KingWulfgar', 'iTunes', 1, 'Soooo slow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 15:49:53'),
	(306, 'Just the volume setting is unbearable now. It used to work logically and well. Now you can’t use the phones vol buttons and the actual volume is no longer shown, just and icon that’s laggy when you touch it, and the volume level is hidden UNDER your finger.  I end up tapping several times, often lowering the volume when I want to raise it.  You now also get errors that you are playing on is already on a different device and you have to agree to kill the player in the other room. Why?  Why can’t I play on all 6 Alexa devices at once? There isn’t even an option to buy multi room playback.', 'Rebel1996', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa keeps getting worse.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 17:01:33'),
	(307, 'The is growing. It would be great if amazon paired up with a search engine to so that i didn’t have to own google smart Home too. It would also be nice if you could communicate through the nest cams not just view.', 'TeamCrowned', 'iTunes', 3, 'Needed updateds', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 17:25:58');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(308, 'since the past few updates, the alexa app brings my iphone 6+ on ios 10.3.3 to a halt. also, the shopping list should be quickly accessible from the home screen', 'patapra', 'iTunes', 1, 'brings phone to a halt', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 19:27:57'),
	(309, 'No reason why it has t been updated yet. Come on Amazon!', 'Nucchemist', 'iTunes', 1, 'Need iPhone X Support!!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 21:23:44'),
	(310, 'Each update makes this app worse.  Freezes more often then not, connecting to smart home devices fails (used to be flawless).', 'K2Kevin', 'iTunes', 2, 'With each update...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 22:12:50'),
	(311, 'Adding and removing devices is still difficult. Navigating app can be frustrating.', 'mattnorton2u', 'iTunes', 1, 'Layout of app needs to be redesigned', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 23:23:10'),
	(312, 'I wish the app had an extra tab for games and fun, it would make getting to it easier than going through all those tabs! Please put games you have in there too, I don’t really rember what games I have now... needs some improvement Amazon, good luck!', 'RoniHiCat', 'iTunes', 3, 'Good, needs more addition too it.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-31 23:51:50'),
	(313, 'Just got Alexa like less then two months ago. The app worked fine at first but then started to stop working. I can’t even open it. I even redownlouded it. I don’t know what else to do.', 'Alicia Hargesheimer', 'iTunes', 1, 'I can’t even get app to work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 00:28:28'),
	(314, 'Aside from this app being extremely slow (taking up to 5 minutes to load a single setting), it also crashes constantly and just generally doesn’t work. I wasted 3 hours just trying to connect my echo dot to the internet. I expect so much more from amazon. Hopefully amazon is working on fixing the problems but I don’t see it happening because of how many problems there are.', '66cj66', 'iTunes', 1, 'Needs serious improvement', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 01:26:38'),
	(315, 'Really, 3-4 months in and no iPhone X support', 'Awesomechineseboy', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 07:18:25'),
	(316, 'App is okay. Please update it to be optimized for the iPhone X!', 'kevescaliente', 'iTunes', 3, 'Okay', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 14:24:02'),
	(317, 'This app is most basic in function. most of the services the app developer claims it can do are false. None of the a music services work as advertised or even work at all!', 'Mrloathing', 'iTunes', 1, 'Amazon Alexa app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 15:10:15'),
	(318, 'I have the app and I’m unable to move past the screen asking we to merge my contacts which I said Later. The App doesn’t respond after I soft reset the phone. Poor app neat device.', 'Mulvie79', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone 10 issues', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 16:05:45'),
	(319, 'I was given an Amazon Echo Show for Christmas. I am now trying to download my contact list. However, my phone is to old to upgrade to an iso 9.0 or better. So, I thought download from my iPad (it much newer)....problem, I don’t seem to have the brains to do that......can I pick someone’s brain on this subject please???? Thank You', 'stuck in no mans land', 'iTunes', 4, 'Help!!!!!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 18:31:58'),
	(320, 'This new update is awful! I can’t find the screen to add skills, it just shows what I’ve already done on it today. Can’t stand it.', 'HappyCat12345', 'iTunes', 1, 'Update is terrible!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 18:58:18'),
	(321, 'The app does not support tablet functionality with the ability to use all capabilities of the echo spot (using camera, two way communication or drop in capability).', 'Lan-Lan', 'iTunes', 1, 'Intuitive?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 19:30:51'),
	(322, 'Either apple throttles it or amazons gotten worse coding. Very slow performance, almost unusable', 'tbarn', 'iTunes', 2, 'Something is wrong here', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 19:30:40'),
	(323, 'I have musicUnlimited and would really like to have the ability to search with in the unlimited section.not just browse. 2. I would also like to be able to manually choose to make a song my alarm. I also like the screened Echoes better. It’s much easier to ask for artist and their music. And we get lyrics now. The echo show and echo spot are my favorites now.', 'lovingorca', 'iTunes', 4, 'Alexa App.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 21:38:21');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(324, 'Latest update seems to have removed the group option for Smart Home when setting up a routine.  Love the new “Alexa says” option. Much better than “okay”.', 'Dan in KC', 'iTunes', 5, 'Groups missing in Routines', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-01 22:06:14'),
	(325, 'First the good I love the shopping list and how it updates works great for a working family for some one to add something while your shopping BUT the rest of the app is junk my biggest issue is the smart home part. It is slow and unreliable controlling devices not directly paired to the echo plus hub. When we are away from home it controls devices about half the time as well as the routines only work about half the time even on my home wifi. Even though I can Open the Hue app or the Wink app and make everything work like it should on the first try but going through the Alexa app it\'s a 50-50 shot', 'Jlom 09', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa app NEEDs WORK', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 03:45:13'),
	(326, 'There needs to be a way to manually tell Alexa I want to play on my home Echo group.\n\nI don’t know why Amazon can’t seem to figure out how to create a “cast” option from the Amazon Music app, or embed the Amazon music app inside of the Alexa app.  I know there is a half integration where I can specify the artist, but I need the fidelity level to get playlists, artist, albums, genres, things like that.\n\nAlexa can’t seem to find some albums or songs when I ask her to play it on a group, but if I ask her the exact same question without the group command she finds it just fine.  Annoying.', 'Bentley_J', 'iTunes', 2, 'Needs direct play option', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 06:19:44'),
	(327, 'I really like the routines options because it allows for multiple actions with a single command. But there are very minimum actions that can be used in routines. One that would make a reasonable feature into an awesome one would be to open and play a preset audible book and if it allowed for a time limit that would be icing on the cake.', 'Pro682', 'iTunes', 3, 'Cool new feature some missing new features', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 06:55:35'),
	(328, 'Alexa app can no longer control my smartplugs. They still work correctly directly through Smart Life app so I know there is nothing wrong with the outlets or their connection to WiFi.', 'Rubberchicken12', 'iTunes', 4, 'Version 880 broke Smart Life integration', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 09:10:01'),
	(329, 'I had all devices working and now none work with latest update!!! I use smart life app to set up and nothing works. Alexa keeps saying OK but cannot turn any devices anymore. PLEASE FIX IMMEDIATELY.', 'Mike14120', 'iTunes', 1, 'Everything is now broken!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 09:19:55'),
	(330, 'Just updated my app and now I can’t even open it. I get an error message and then the login screen, but when I click login nothing happens. So... completely useless.', 'gidget2282', 'iTunes', 1, 'App stopped working', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 12:48:01'),
	(331, 'Meh', 'Formerbarista', 'iTunes', 3, 'Not updated for iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 15:10:27'),
	(332, 'If you can’t wait to hear: “Alexa cannot connect to your WiFi Network” 35 times, then this is the product for you!!', 'Hell yes it\'s loaded.', 'iTunes', 1, 'Does not connect. Get the Google product.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 16:52:14'),
	(333, 'This app has always been bad when trying to set up Echo. However, I\'ve always been able to get it to connect to the network eventually. Not today, apparently. I\'ve literally spent hours. Between closing and restarting the app, resetting the device with a paper clip and just waiting for the process to fail, I\'ve gotten nowhere. Not sure what kind of network is needed, maybe one with no passwords? The app interface is just bad UX, plain and simple. Hit a back button and end up on the Home screen. Try to join a pw protected network and wait for the connection to fail so you can finally see the password prompt. Complete setup and you are stuck on a video tutorial screen. Once you get the thing working, the device is great (not the app). Just pray you don\'t ever need to set up again. With all of Bezos\' billions, you\'d think they could hire some real developers and UX designers.', 'uncleridiculous725216', 'iTunes', 1, 'Can\'t connect', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 19:01:41');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(334, 'This app is unusable after the update, iPhone X issue?', 'S.Lebowski', 'iTunes', 1, 'Stuck at Permissions View', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 19:20:18'),
	(335, 'Time to update app for iPhone X resolution.', 'c2k4rx8', 'iTunes', 2, 'iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 19:22:28'),
	(336, 'Is not working', 'Sfinxme', 'iTunes', 1, 'A crap', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 22:32:59'),
	(337, 'I bought 3 echo dots. And they changed the ability that be able to stream on more than 1 device. Feel like I got scammed.', 'Last biking', 'iTunes', 1, 'Scam', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-02 23:17:19'),
	(338, 'Far everything Alexa does right, it makes the shortcomings even more glaring. \n\nEspecially when it comes to smart home features. When it comes to automation, I don’t want everything to happen the second I say a command. For instance, if I say “I’m leaving the house”. I want Alexa to wait until I’m out of the house before it locks the door. Easily fixed by adding a “wait 30 seconds” ability. \n\nAlso frustrated that the only info I can get from a flash briefing are skills that are specifically made for flash briefing. Any question that I can ask Alexa, skill or not, should be able to pipe the answer to the flash briefing.', 'Scott_H_Wilder', 'iTunes', 3, 'Great app. Could be better', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 00:42:41'),
	(339, '1 star until I can use the settings tab.\n\nI can’t connect my dot from an iPhone and it’s gotta get sorted out or we’re gonna take it back.', 'MAndersonComedy', 'iTunes', 1, 'Buggy, can’t connect', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 01:12:35'),
	(340, 'Ever since this app update my echo no longer connects to the internet.', 'ssadfsdf', 'iTunes', 1, 'Echo can’t connect to internet', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 01:13:58'),
	(341, 'I love my Alexa but the app is so fricken slow and I cannot manage anything without it taking forever to load.', 'Moms-account', 'iTunes', 3, 'Slow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 02:08:17'),
	(342, 'Replaced it with same echo 2nd gen and it still only points towards its power cord in the middle of a dead quiet room no matter where I stand. After I spent 2 hours setting up my 16 different hue lights the new one didn’t port that info and I don’t feel like doing it again. UPS return label peeling off the printer right now.', 'Allenheights', 'iTunes', 1, 'LED points in one direction only. Can’t hear me.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 02:14:59'),
	(343, 'Today when I get back from work, I can NOT turn lights on through Alexa!?!? \n\nWhat’s wrong with this latest update? All my TP-Link smart plugs (which was purchased as a bundle with Echo Dot) does not work with Alexa anymore!!!!\n\nThe only way I can turn my lights on are through TP-Link Kasa app.....\n\nReally disappointed to this stupid update by Amazon. Especially when they FALSELY stated that “You can now add devices easily to smart homes” what a JOKE...', 'macakacheck', 'iTunes', 1, 'Latest update turns SMART home to DUMB home', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 02:25:54'),
	(344, 'Out of the many issues I can touch on, one really bugs me. A L A R M S! As soon as I hit the alarm and reminder button, and then proceed to change the sound and time of an alarm, it freezes. I can’t use it at all in any way! After restarting the app and trying everything and all, nothing. I’m using an iPhone 6S mind you.', 'Eatingsawdust', 'iTunes', 1, 'I’m trying to like it, but that is not happening', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 02:54:39'),
	(345, 'It was not easy to set up but I finally did.  I loved the app since I got it because of the routines that could be used with Echo Dot however it is now having problems.  One of my devices which is working perfectly under Kasa is no longer responsive under Alexa app which means the echo is not understanding it.  All other devices are fine except this one... it seems to be temperamental.', 'Mazenhelkhatib', 'iTunes', 2, 'Temper-mental', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 04:04:37'),
	(346, 'Amazon really needs to scrap this app and start over. Very clunky and not user friendly. Just doesn’t feel right and definitely not up to Amazon standards.', 'craig1021', 'iTunes', 2, 'Amazon is better than this app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 04:50:52');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(347, 'I bought this echo dot for christmas gift, but it constantly makes problems and not connected very well. :( feels awful', '모모몽비', 'iTunes', 1, 'An unstable device', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 11:05:02'),
	(348, 'I think some of the skill integration could be better. For example, I use the trackr app to find my phone. When I ask Alexa to find my phone, she’ll say something like “there are several skills I can find your phone with...” and goes on to explain that that trackr app can find my phone. I already know this because the skill is downloaded and the app is linked. Then she’ll proceed to ask me what I want to do. I’ll again say “find my phone” and then she’ll make it ring. It just seems like more dialogue hoops to jump through than necessary. I don’t think anything compares to Alexa right now, but it’d be nice to have the feeling that it “just works”.\nAlso, optimization for iPhone X should have been implemented already, Amazon is late to the game with that. I’ll bump it up another star once they do that.', 'Calvillar', 'iTunes', 3, 'Needs some work.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 14:52:48'),
	(349, 'Very difficult erasing history..   too many glitches for what is supposed to be a good app', 'hypothysis', 'iTunes', 1, 'Me', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 15:16:35'),
	(350, 'I wish when you set a reminder with Echo that it would badge the Alexa app so I could actually use the reminder feature away from my echo', 'Trey902', 'iTunes', 4, 'Badges for Echo Please', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 16:40:17'),
	(351, 'Echo dot=amazing. App=3 stars. When I want to connect something it keeps make ping me redo it or saying \'\' app not supported\'\'. Update it now or support it', 'Jeff Job Bob', 'iTunes', 3, 'Not supported', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 21:11:00'),
	(352, 'Connectivity issues after 12-30-17 update', 'Tydvg2468', 'iTunes', 1, 'Buggy update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 22:52:50'),
	(353, 'The interface is slow even when connected to fast WiFi and internet. \n\nAs for privacy, I should be able to enter contacts manually. I don’t want to “periodically” upload all my contacts to Amazon just so I can call my parents on their Echo. Amazon has no business collecting all my contacts just so I can call one.', 'deepsoul13', 'iTunes', 1, 'Slow and poor privacy', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-03 22:54:47'),
	(354, 'I love my echo! But the app itself is super slow and I’m using my iPhone X hooked to my second generation echo', 'Minecrafter0117', 'iTunes', 3, 'Slow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 00:47:43'),
	(355, 'The entire page is glitch filled. Now there is no way to add skills.  I used to have endless screens to peruse, but now I only have a black screen.  The only screen I can use is the home page that just shows what I’ve asked Alexa to do by voice.', 'TammyDeWitt', 'iTunes', 1, 'The app is dissolving to nothing', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 00:59:41'),
	(356, 'In my opinion, (and this is just a personal preference of mine- some people might not care) there should be a setting or feature to hide activity from other echo devices in your history feed. Not only do I find it annoying that I see my family’s echo history, I kinda feel like we’re all invading each other’s privacy by being able to see it. I’d really like a feature to turn this off.', 'josepharrrts', 'iTunes', 3, 'Advice for developers:', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 02:29:47'),
	(357, 'Terrible App.  Not worth the hassle.   Returning it ASAP.   Tried re-downloading it several times', 'Firsttimeparents', 'iTunes', 1, 'Always crashes and is slow.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 02:32:57');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(358, 'This app is without a doubt the worst, slowest, least responsive, badly engineered app that I have ever seen. You can literally spend over an hour trying to connect WiFi to your Tap without success. The app slowly, agonizingly takes you from one step to the next before freezing. \nI’d like to blame it on the slowness of the Fire, but it’s no better on my iPhone. And that’s with full WiFi reception. \n\nHowever, if you’re not successful you can always call their help dept. and speak to a rep. The one that I got was minimally conversant in English and had what sounded like an Indian accent- as did all the other people in the room. Her help consisted of reading a manual to me - covering things that had no relevance to my problem.   Not surprisingly, I received no help. \n\nI did, however, receive an email from Amazon with a request to complete a survey. I complied, explaining my problem and basically asking that they call me. Of course, they did not call. \n\nNow don’t get me wrong. I am an Amazon Prime member and am happy with their Prime program, including Prime Pantry. I have, to this date, purchased three Taps, eight Fires and a Dot, most as gifts. \n\nBut after my experiences with this app and their customer support I have come to an unavoidable conclusion. \n\nIt’s time to try Google.', 'PaulD Esq', 'iTunes', 1, 'Time to try Google', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 03:01:55'),
	(359, 'So we have an Echo, an Echo Version 2, two dots, a Hue Bridge, eight Hue bulbs and two Iris’s and everything was working fine. \n\nUsing an iPhone 7S Plus running iOS 11.2.1 I updated the Alexa app yesterday (Jan 3, 2018) and it factory reset everything in the house. Alexa could not find any Amazon devices, smart home devices or groups. Hugely inconvenient considering everything was set up and perfect the day before. \n\nI guess it’s my fault for becoming dependent on home automation but it goes to show how fickle it all can be when it goes haywire.', 'Marnitauras', 'iTunes', 3, 'App update 2.2.880.0 reset every device', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 03:20:52'),
	(360, 'Today, all my WeMo and TP LINK aren’t responding with Alexa even though I can control those smart switches with their corresponding apps.  Resetting Alexa, Smart switches, router, Echo Dot, Smartphone, none of them helps.  Alexa app also doesn’t work after sign in and crashes back to home page', 'iPhone JP', 'iTunes', 1, 'App constantly crashes with iPhone X iOS11.2.5', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 04:34:34'),
	(361, 'I love using Alexa, and the app made it even better indeed. It gives most of the control you would need to use Alexa and enjoy it, especially the routines 👍👍, and groups. The only problem I can\'t fix is the Smart home options that won\'t discover my lights or entertainment system, although when I go to the webpage app, it works perfectly fine.\nI hope for more updates and improvemnts, PLEASE SURPRISE ME AMAZON', 'Fbabtain', 'iTunes', 4, 'Very nice BUT!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 10:15:55'),
	(362, 'iPhone x update sorely needed. Most other Amazon apps have been updated already.', 'b-lake624', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X update needed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 18:02:40'),
	(363, 'I’m giving the app 1 star solely for the lack of iPhone X screen support. The phone came out November 3rd, 2017... your main app supports the screen... what’s the hold up?', 'TheGirlIsZelda', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X is a thing....', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 19:13:28'),
	(364, 'Why is this page blank ? I am trying to connect my Roomba Vacuum and nothing shows up on this page', 'Kenslady', 'iTunes', 1, 'Skills', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 19:32:58'),
	(365, 'I received an Alexa item for Christmas. I set it up (took several attempts) through my cell phone as a hotspot. It consistently offline each morning and doesn’t reconnect to what I already set up. The network is saved, and when I click on “connect” nothing.\n\nThis app is cumbersome, complicated, and should be an embarrassment to Amazon. Shame on you for being the number 1 retailer and putting such a poor product out.', 'tobtrejo', 'iTunes', 1, 'Offline', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 20:38:56');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(366, 'When I saw how alexa work and everything you could do with it I was I\'m and exited to try it out. By following that let me tell you I have never written a review and now I\'m taking my time to say that the Alexa software and equipment are incredible, but this map is pure garbage. It crashes, it\'s super slow, doesn\'t save your settings preferences, and I could keep on all day saying stuff that fails to do, but since I have more important things to do, like returning the equipment and erasing this crap out of my phone until you guys decide to hire someone more capable to design your app, I\'ll leave it at here.', 'Galactus90', 'iTunes', 1, 'Disappointment', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 20:46:03'),
	(367, 'The iPhone X has been out for several months now and there is still no support for the new screen. Please add support for the iPhone X and fix some major bugs! 😁', 'bocaJ930', 'iTunes', 4, 'Come on!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 21:08:08'),
	(368, 'Given all the negative reviews I’m wondering if Amazon even reads them. Unless you just say Alexa, what’s the weather tonight you can look for cool temperatures, OK I’m not even fixing that as she just typed it right out.  That is about as much as she can handle, or what’s my update; otherwise this device has become increasingly stupid since the original came out.  It’s really shocking, truth be told. We own so many of these devices it’s  embarrassing. The latest being the echo show which was a Christmas gift from my son. She doesn’t know anything; she clearly has it going to I’m not saying the name of the company yet because she’ll start talking school yet. I don’t know what his happened did they ship these devices with absolutely no knowledge built in. The fact that you cannot  easily  link an iOS device is horrid, you CANNOT WATCH YouTube VIDEOS on the ECHO SHOW which apparently you ONCE could, DISGUSTS ME. \nI know people with the GOOGLE DEVICE,  and let me tell you, GOOGLE KNOWS THE ANSWER! \nLastly,  would you update your skills to 2018?? I tried several today and deleted every single one.  Alexa is a downer.', 'liebly', 'iTunes', 1, 'Stop making new devices.  FIX YOUR OPERATING SYTSTEM,  OR LACK THEREOF.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 21:41:44'),
	(369, 'All these frequent updates but not one optimized for the iPhone X!', 'jeffcny_', 'iTunes', 2, 'iPhone X?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 23:20:01'),
	(370, 'I have Alexa setup to play routines to turn on and off my lights, it worked for a couple of days then stopped working. Alexa only responded “okay” but didn’t take any action. It’s still not working after updating the app. Please fix', 'L我就看看', 'iTunes', 3, 'Alexa stopped playing routines', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 23:36:15'),
	(371, 'Every time I open the app it tries to get me to setup messaging. I have no clue where to go, and I’ve looked like crazy. My recommendation is to hold off on updating to this version if you have no plans to use messaging through your echo devices.', 'deathraylabs', 'iTunes', 1, 'no, you don’t get my contacts, alexa!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-04 23:47:44'),
	(372, 'The app won’t open. I’ve tried everything. I can get to the home page but anything after that and it keeps searching like it isn’t connected. Please fix this bug!!!!', 'Todopants', 'iTunes', 1, 'What is happening with this app?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 00:27:15'),
	(373, 'I got software 2.3.888.0 today and now, all of a sudden, my Echo and Echo Dot can no longer communicate with my WEMO switches. Early today all was well, but now Alexa thinks all my WEMO switches are unresponsive. They are still on the network because I can control them with WEMO app.', 'John1425J', 'iTunes', 1, 'Bad update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 02:21:44'),
	(374, 'Just finding out how wonderful a tool Alexa is!', 'tomski47', 'iTunes', 5, 'Great', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 04:23:10'),
	(375, 'Needs an update so it fits the screen for the iPhone X', 'Bree:D', 'iTunes', 2, 'Needs iPhone X update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 04:25:43'),
	(376, 'Come on Amazon! This is getting ridiculous.', 'LazaroFilm', 'iTunes', 1, 'Still not iPhone X optimized.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 04:30:09'),
	(377, 'Alexa Messaging has mysteriously been removed from the iPad version of the app. Hard to imagine why.', 'kolebee', 'iTunes', 1, 'Wait, where did messaging go?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 04:37:21');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(378, 'No iPhone X support. Only the “Amazon” app has been updated to support the screen. Shows the priorities.', 'Leptz', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 05:36:01'),
	(379, 'Only had Alexa for a month now, but it’s getting worse.  It keeps duplicating devices and although I found a workaround, it still glitches, but music played just fine.  Then yesterday my music groups stopped working and we’re dropping devices as “unreachable.”  Looks like an update.  I bought too many devices to return, but can still not recommend it to friends.  Too glitchy.', 'EdTheReal', 'iTunes', 2, 'Getting Worse - Very Disappointed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 15:51:00'),
	(380, 'can you add a text box to search, instead of relying on the voice control. it is helpful when searching for a song to play while a song is playing and not interrupting the song. \n\nthank you', 'Rei07', 'iTunes', 4, 'text box', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 17:43:31'),
	(381, 'Controlling the Echo through the app is everything!\n*Can u please make the volume button more user friendly? It’s in an odd spot and does not respond well. (It’s probably the most used button in the app but holds very little real estate at the moment)\n\n*please add a search feature. Would be good to be able to set the next request for music by typing it in as opposed to always shouting across the room.\n\nThank you.', 'gggminman', 'iTunes', 3, 'Control your music.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 18:35:20'),
	(382, 'I don’t know why people give low stars for this app. You just need to know how to operate it. So far, I was able to control all my home appliances with Alexa. Couldn’t be happier', 'Johnl872', 'iTunes', 5, 'Best app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 18:37:47'),
	(383, 'Just updated. Now it doesn\'t work. It\'s stuck on a page asking about permissions.', 'Ufxitxirxtix', 'iTunes', 1, 'Don\'t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 20:20:17'),
	(384, 'This is totally useless. Who ever set this app up is not very good. I supposedly linked my probe to my Echo and it can’t change channels it just regurgitate what I said. \nThis app down right stinks!', 'disappointment to the Max', 'iTunes', 1, 'Useless App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 20:54:05'),
	(385, 'I used to be able to say echo drop in on kids dot, it used to work now echo says I can’t find a contact named that. Podcasts are now more difficult, books are difficult, you broke Alexa. \n\nRoll it back!', 'Urgh99', 'iTunes', 1, 'Latest update should be rolled back', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-05 21:51:02'),
	(386, 'Some definite issues. iPhone X, I am unable to update location setting in the app. The keyboard closes soon as I press add or edit location. Stock keyboard. Tried deregistering echo. Will try uninstall, reinstall now.', 'MrBrownSound', 'iTunes', 3, 'Issues', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 01:21:03'),
	(387, 'Makes my phone hot and doesn’t work', 'Mkrage134', 'iTunes', 1, 'Slow and buggy', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 01:22:54'),
	(388, 'Ok but needs better functionality. Keeps needing to reinstall at allowing permissions and signing out.', 'Psychified', 'iTunes', 2, 'Meh', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 01:27:17'),
	(389, 'This app is buggy! It locks up. It doesn’t interface with the device well. It keeps asking for a password then crashes.  Its really not good.  The echo plus is awesome but the app is just no where near the same par.', 'Lordvader3000', 'iTunes', 1, 'The device is great the app not so much', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 02:12:34'),
	(390, 'Searching for music is not easy. Don’t like this apps lack of controls.', 'earlyd', 'iTunes', 1, 'More controls needed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 03:06:39'),
	(391, 'Clunky, hard to use, takes FOREVER to load sometimes. Dashboard is useless (I know what I asked Alexa, I just said it thanks). Features that should have easy access don’t... it’s just a mess. And on top of that THEY DONT EVEN HAVE IT OPTIMIZED FOR IPHONE X. Come on guys literally my little off brand chinese smart home app optimized for the iPhone X LETS GO. Love amazon but this is one of my least favorites. Contacted them about the issues and got an email back proceeding to tell me I was wrong about everything in very broken English... *sigh* okay I’m done here. Suffer with it, we must.', 'jami99', 'iTunes', 1, 'Google home app blows this out of the water', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 07:29:16');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(392, 'I can’t select multiple groups due to the fact they’re grayed out under Alexa enable devices. I set one group of lights up but can’t set others up. It use to work prior to the update. Please fix!!!!!', '~Val~', 'iTunes', 3, 'Alexa enable devices grayed out.....', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 09:01:33'),
	(393, 'Since this update when I use drop in from my iPhone to the echo show it says “My Echo Show isn’t using a video enabled device,” it worked just fine before this update.', 'KareBear1959', 'iTunes', 2, 'iPhone and Echo Show', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 09:28:19'),
	(394, 'Needs better integration with amazon music. Should be able to easily select my favorite playlists.', 'aj2k7', 'iTunes', 3, 'Where are my amazon music playlists???', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 10:54:34'),
	(395, 'This app looks like it’s made by the intern on Friday afternoon. It’s hard to use and has super weird user interface / UX. Do people at Amazon test their apps? Do they use it? Navigation is slow and functions are hard to find. It has super weird interface choices to manage your smart home with discovery and 3 different tabs like devices, routines and scenes. The only thing I want is to turn on and off my TV, not drive the space shuttle. I don’t think a normal person will be able to figure it out. \n\nAlso it’s January 2018 and there’s no iPhone X version. Clearly not a priority.\n\nAmazon come on, you’re a huge company - maybe hire a few UX designers and IOS developers? It’s not that Alexa is light sold product which doesn’t deserve attention. This is more an embarrassment than anything else.', 'rdschouw', 'iTunes', 1, 'Amazon should be ashamed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 14:45:12'),
	(396, 'Glitches or bugs or whatever they’re called. I keep encountering them whenever I play music. Never refreshes when my music is updated on the queue, so instead I close and restart the app. Very annoying.', '_FAT_BOY_SLIM', 'iTunes', 1, 'Still needs improvements', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 19:03:25'),
	(397, 'Search for a skill, and the sole result will appear below the bottom bar, so you have to scroll through unused space to see it. Reminds me of all the weird bugs in Calibre.', 'gavinbeatty', 'iTunes', 2, 'Basic little bugs all round', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 19:23:23'),
	(398, 'The screen still appears to be like and iPhone 8 or 8 Plus and older.', 'JaydenBomback123', 'iTunes', 3, 'iPhone X optimization???', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 19:42:26'),
	(399, 'App no longer responds. Very frustrating!  Have tried restarting several times and have the same result.', 'FlashDanz', 'iTunes', 1, 'Last wat update has locked my app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 22:20:40'),
	(400, 'The amazon Alexa is a wonderful tool to use however I have the IPhone X and the app isn’t compatible with it   Please make it compatible within the next update', 'Judah Howard', 'iTunes', 5, 'Wonderful App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 23:11:58'),
	(401, 'The app still isn’t optimized and when you link your account with skills it’s shrinks it so much it’s hard to use some of the APIs.', 'Kda1990j', 'iTunes', 1, 'Optimize it for iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 23:46:14'),
	(402, 'We need this app to pause a timer? Really? When did this start? It makes using this feature cumbersome and pointless.', 'istuart45', 'iTunes', 1, 'Dumbing down echo to force this crap app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 00:09:35'),
	(403, 'I just did the update and now can not connect to any switches in my house. Please fix this every thing worked perfectly before the update. Don’t update people reading this', 'Lerloke', 'iTunes', 1, 'Horrible', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 00:30:34');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(404, 'Amazon the king of shopping and information collect completely missed this one.  As an Amazon shopper and prime member, you would expect that you could just use your Amazon account information to sign into this app and All would be good.  Well not so fast, I have had to add my information into this app four times now and none with autofill boxes available.  This app is far from state of the art or even current state of apps.  It was so disappointing to have to manually manage everything when Amazon already has the information.  It seems like they had the hardware done and the software was an after thought.  I could go on a week with the critic of this and I have only messed with it for the last five hours.  Hope it gets better with the updates because it has been beyond disappointing so far!', '4.99 down the drain', 'iTunes', 1, 'A long ways to go', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 00:55:09'),
	(405, 'I still love my Echo and now my Echo Show but this app has become utterly useless.', 'LTyson5', 'iTunes', 1, 'Hate this new app...', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 03:32:14'),
	(406, 'I love my Alexa but the app doesn’t even work. I can’t even set my alarm from my phone anymore. The app constantly freezes up and continues to not work. Even when I delete it and re-download it it doesn’t work. I constantly can’t even check or change my alarms manually.', 'Georgia sun', 'iTunes', 1, 'App doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 03:59:25'),
	(407, 'On two occasions have spent two+ hours attempting to connect Echo Dot.  App hangs or errors out w cryptic codes.', 'Art1950', 'iTunes', 1, 'Virtually worthless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 04:55:05'),
	(408, 'While I love the Echo Dot, the Alexa app has a major privacy flaw. It automatically uploads any contact that also has Alexa app. This is weird,  I don’t want my realtor my dentist etc. to be able to call me on my home Echo.\nThe other thing is that if you have enabled a Household, then everyone shares contacts. There is no privacy!\nCustomers/App users should have a way to be able to hide select contacts.\nI’m sure my adult son doesn’t want me seeing all of his contacts , and I certainly don’t want him seeing all of my contacts.\n I don’t know thought of this but it certainly not cool.\nThat app it’s self is very clunky very hard to understand and get around. I think they need a new development team. And fast before people start giving up and switch to google assistant.', 'Don\'t update it ruins it!', 'iTunes', 1, 'Privacy concerns are major!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 06:12:01'),
	(409, 'Overall, the app works well(ie not crashing), but it is terribly organized, and it takes me forever to get anything done with it.', 'Jake.Norris170', 'iTunes', 3, 'Not At All Well Organized', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 14:39:15'),
	(410, 'amazon this app is trash. doesn’t work', 'M-SWAGGGGGG', 'iTunes', 1, 'trash', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 14:54:39'),
	(411, 'iPhone X not yet supported.', 'ELKAHLOUT', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 15:21:43'),
	(412, 'Sick of this app trying to force me to add messaging. Nobody to message so cut the crap. Better read the fine print on that option. Don\'t waste your money on this echo stuff. Buy Apple I bet they\'ll get it right. Can someone answer a question for me? Is this app not working right or do they force you to sign up for messaging now before you can  do anything else. Apple only lets you see 5 or 6 reviews which the rest are just as bad I’m willing to bet. No live customer support. I don’t know about yours but my echo show comes on by itself sometimes. So if I sign up for messages and it comes on it records what is being said. Matter of fact you don’t even have to have messages and it records everything that is being said when it wakes up. Wonder if it records video when it wakes up on something not even close to a wake up word.', 'Questabond', 'iTunes', 1, 'Sick', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 16:52:46');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(413, 'I know there are some smart people on your team, it seems to me that someone in management who doesn’t actually use the device and is completely out of touch with the user market is making all the decisions. Please keep the intended user market in mind with this app. You have an amazing product and you are ruining it. Get some real world user groups and pay attention to what they have to say and observe how they interact with the product. Don’t make me sell my Alexa and google 🤕', 'dabigbozman', 'iTunes', 2, 'Developers plz read', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 17:30:14'),
	(414, 'It is impossible to add about half of my Smart Home devices to a new routine. No explanation, no logic. They\'re all listed in Smart Home menu but don\'t appear in available list. You can\'t play music, stop music, add Stringify actions from/to routines. What a pile of 💩, the app feels and works as if it was programmed by a proverbial monkey with a typewriter!', 'tabaks', 'iTunes', 1, 'Useless junk, zero value', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 17:33:34'),
	(415, 'The app is hard to use by design. It pretty easy to get lost and have no way to get back to a previous screen. There is a lot here but it is too difficult to get to or discover what you might find useful. The conversations tab is major real estate dedicated to a feature I don’t want to use often or at all.  \n\nThen the bugs - unresponsiveness, errors, \nYou can add a tunein favorite but you can’t remove it. What does Queue do besides show what is currently playing (already shown elsewhere) and flash a bit when I navigate to this tab?\n\nThere s great potential here and the alexa technology is truly amazing. It’s just too bad that this app hinders the experience so much. I have to believe AMZ is working on a total replacement.', 'wolfpacker', 'iTunes', 2, 'Bad user experience and chock full of bugs', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 18:59:24'),
	(416, 'Why are the developers taking features away? First I noticed I can no longer look into a playlist without it starting, stopping the music I already had playing. Now today I noticed I can’t add songs to a cue “play this song next” etc. that had been taken away too. I thought updates were supposed to improve the app not make it worse.', 'Dan J Allard', 'iTunes', 1, 'Stop taking features away', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 22:10:30'),
	(417, 'I am not sure if it is my phone but the app won’t update', 'dancer_248', 'iTunes', 2, 'New Update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 22:46:45'),
	(418, 'Currently about half the menu links result in a blank white screen with black bars at the top and bottom; the other half work. I have strong network and WiFi connections and waiting up to 5 minutes doesn’t result in any content. I’m trying to enable a new “skill” so that I can give voice commands about a new smart device. I tried asking Alexa to do it verbally but she told me to use the app. If I wanted to do something else in the app such as use an existing device, I might give it more stars as that link is currently producing a working page. (Another reviewer suggests that the problems of those who are having difficulty with the app are our own fault for being incompetent and not Googling for a solution. Although I don’t think this should be necessary if an app is well-designed, Google is always my first resource. There is no solution suggested for a complete lack of content in random areas.)', 'Sventare', 'iTunes', 2, 'Half unusable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-07 23:58:20'),
	(419, 'I was so excited when they finally added multiroom music for Spotify, I love Spotify and would never switch my music subscription even though amazon sure has tried. The multiroom music has so many glitches I’ve had to regroup my echos 5 times now to fix the glitches, right as I type this 2 of my 4 echos are playing music the other 2 aren’t, for no reason at all, I tried unplugging them and resetting them, didn’t fix the issue, I go into the Alexa app and it says they are all ready to be used in my music everywhere group, very buggy.', 'BearsIn3D', 'iTunes', 3, 'Fix Spotify', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 01:03:23');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(420, 'My echo dots were working good controlling all my smart home devices until today. Now, everything I ask it to do it keeps saying “sorry that device doesn’t support that”. I have reset my devices and set them all up as new and still NOPE.  I guess I am going to have to trade Alexa in for Google home. Just when I was getting ready to expand my devices, good timing to stop me.', 'Greg you', 'iTunes', 1, 'Was working fine until now', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 03:41:00'),
	(421, 'I love falling asleep to rain and thunder', 'Lalamedix', 'iTunes', 5, 'Relax', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 07:04:37'),
	(422, 'Was working great but with every update gets more and more buggy. Very frustrating.', 'Melaroo7', 'iTunes', 2, 'Was working', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 07:20:16'),
	(423, 'Since the few updates that have been made my settings won’t open or my skills in my app!!!??? What’s going on? Pls FIX THIS ISSUE!!! We need to use this for our Alexia machine or what’s the point!!!!', 'Anabel Jordan', 'iTunes', 4, 'Since the few updates doesn’t can’t open anything!!!! FIX IT!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 13:48:43'),
	(424, 'How does a company like Amazon have such a piss-poor product and application? The app crashes, search function is a JOKE, and it is Beyond slow...when it works. Get it right!', 'Ntharder', 'iTunes', 1, 'Come On!! Get It Right!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 15:41:40'),
	(425, 'I use a iPhone X on the latest update. It’s not optimized for my device.', 'X-47C', 'iTunes', 3, 'Meh', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 18:37:18'),
	(426, 'This is a great app I would recommend it to everybody I know', 'Fyredozer', 'iTunes', 5, 'Mr', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 18:50:01'),
	(427, 'I was excited for Alexa... but. The app is slow. I can get off the couch and turn the light bulb faster than this POS. Setup on the app was horrible. Come on Amazon', 'acaq313', 'iTunes', 1, 'Boo', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-08 23:58:25'),
	(428, 'Please update to support iPhone X! The screen needs to be optimized! Also, clean up the app so it’s less buggy and runs fast and smooth. The animations take too long and are outdated. Thanks and I hope you consider my requests.', 'iceicejick', 'iTunes', 1, 'Please fix!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-09 00:29:30'),
	(429, 'No where to add bookmarks or seamlessly stop/resume between Alexa devices.', 'Markv723', 'iTunes', 3, 'Please improve Audible integration', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-09 02:09:28'),
	(430, 'This app worked well when it was simple and was linked to just one or two devices. Now it’s a mess. \n\nPLEASE separate the lists into a separate app, maybe one with a widget and force press on the app icon support. The app has gotten so bloated and slow to lead that using lists is miserable.\n\nAs Alexa devices have grown more popular, configuring them is a mess. I have and echo, two dogs, five Sonos devices, and a couple Fire TVs. Most settings I’d like to set for all devices, but they’re all separate (without any indication of what TYPE of device they are), and the settings don’t offer a way to share them.\n\nMultiple user profiles are terrible terrible to use; you have to configure all\nYour device groups/names separately!! They don’t share between profiles. And it’s confusing about what does and doesn’t share across profiles.', 'Tabletmeister', 'iTunes', 2, 'Overloaded, bloated', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-09 12:11:04'),
	(431, 'Please stop crippling the Tap with reduced functionality. Add the ability to be part of a music group for multiroom playback. Get rid of the useless as acknowledgement beeps. Add the rest of the wake word options. \n\nThe volume slider omg I can\'t even go there lol.\n\nUpdate: tablet version eats half the screen with "things to try."\nThere needs to be a way to turn that off please.', 'Io333333', 'iTunes', 3, 'Stop treating the tap like a step child', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-09 12:37:14'),
	(432, 'This app is so slow and lags and freezes. I\'ve been trying to connect to my music and it\'s been freezing every time I try. This app really needs work. I keep getting so annoyed with it', 'Lraborn', 'iTunes', 2, 'Needs help', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-09 23:27:58');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(433, 'Every time this app gets updated, simple features get harder and harder to use. Just today, I tried to view how much time was left on my timer by pressing “view timer”, and it took me into this over-engineered tabbed view that listed every single reminder, alarm, and timer that was setup on the dumb thing.\nDreadful.', 'Aveman101', 'iTunes', 1, 'By far the ugliest app installed on my phone', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 00:26:35'),
	(434, 'Can’t swipe to go back. Accidentally tap on the wrong things. It registers taps that were never intended. Not an intuitive UI. This app is a complete pile 🐶💩\nHorrible', '_n8tr', 'iTunes', 1, 'Just awful', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 00:33:05'),
	(435, 'The Amazon Alexa app was working as it should till yesterday’s Apple iSO update. The update is 11.2.2. Good thing I already had my new Alexa Echo set up before this happened. Tried to contact customer support but couldn’t find a way to do so.', 'Likeit111', 'iTunes', 3, 'App stopped working after iSO update 11.2.2', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 02:37:05'),
	(436, 'Good app, please update for iPhone X', 'jmpanugo', 'iTunes', 3, 'Good', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 04:00:14'),
	(437, 'Can’t set alarms anyone without it freezing. PITA.', 'Conversuasionalist', 'iTunes', 1, 'Locks up', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 09:11:56'),
	(438, 'This app continues to freeze. Does not allow for alarm set up on multiple devices without freezing itself. Please fix!', 'PanteraGlo', 'iTunes', 2, 'Alexa...FREEZES', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 10:36:33'),
	(439, 'Love amazon but this app is terrible. Rarely can you use settings and have it actually load the first time. It’s confusing having to reconnect and unconnected from WiFi. Bluetooth doesn’t even work. Wish I would have gone with google home instead.', 'Mich3ll3$', 'iTunes', 1, 'Disappointing', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 13:19:49'),
	(440, 'App does not work well with iOS 11.2.2 - doesn’t find online echo dots or spots. Lags with switching through menu. Amazon engineering really needs to work on this - sometimes you just don’t want to yell commands at your devices.', 'AzDara', 'iTunes', 1, 'App functionality', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 13:40:46'),
	(441, 'All has been working fine on up until today. Alexa will not play my SIRIUS XM App. She keeps telling me to go to settings and link my SIRIUS account. My account has already been linked with the Alexa App. I am a very tech savvy person and never had so much problems with any App but this one. Engineering needs to get their act together. \nAs for the person St Melyd that is a 63 year old non tech granny. You are just one of the lucky ones. I am a 6S IPhone user and there has been issues with this particular model. So lay off of your comments about us “Whiners”. This is a real issue and I have read reviews on SIRIUS XM and other developers and there are problems big time! Get it together Echo/Alexa! \nPS: no problems with the SIRIUS XM App itself. It plays great!', 'HotelCaliforniaGraysCreek', 'iTunes', 1, 'Mary Jane', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 14:45:58'),
	(442, 'My alarm didn’t go off this morning. I asked Alexa alarms are set. She said none. I have had this thing for over a year and the alarms have been set for the same times for at least 6 months, 2 different alarms. I looked at the app this morning which was a job in itself, it was stuck. There were no alarms set and no way to set alarms. I uninstalled and reinstalled. Still nothing. I figured that maybe I had to speak my alarm commands in again. I tried but was told “I can only set a 1 time alarm within the next 24 hours.”  What? I don’t know what happened but whatever it was it’s not good. These glitches or whatever they are need to be fixed or Alexa is going to lose out to Google.', 'Syvellia', 'iTunes', 1, 'What happened?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 17:07:02'),
	(443, 'The app takes 5-6 minutes to load each screen, and times out 20% of the time. Completely unusable.', 'CHICHIYAYAYA', 'iTunes', 1, 'Non functional', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-10 20:27:32'),
	(444, 'This app is total garbage. Glitches have taken over.', 'pissyshark', 'iTunes', 1, 'Garbage', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-11 01:42:40');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(445, 'We initially generally liked the app, although we found it somewhat confusing and unintuitive. Then I was spontaneous logged out of the App while travelling. I was trying to resolve my problem that I could not log on for days. \nI tried repeatedly to login. Aside from the annoying process of having to enter cryptogram images, I tried over and over again to login. Each time the app would look like it was accepting my login, only to return me to a fresh login screen. \nI contacted the “help” desk via chat.  I was passed from representative to representative on chat, with representatives changing, even in the early stages of our conversation and without notice or explanation for the change. I was told to do things that I had told them I had already done. In the end I was told they would send my case to engineering. I received a simple email of things to try while I waited for a response. That email was a restatement of all the things that were all the basic things that the chat “helpers” had stubbornly suggested, even though I had already told them I had done those things. \nAfter again trying to restart my phone, the resumed chat help seemed to have no knowledge of my previous questions. \nFinally, when I heard from engineering I wrote back to say that I had finally gotten the app to connect, for no apparent reason, and after days of trying. \nI asked on question : Does the app not work when traveling outside the USA?\nInstead of getting a reply, I’ve now received another email offering to help “solve my problem”, again with no apparent awareness of my specific situation, and asking me to call. \nI have given hours of my time to this annoying app and unhelpful process. \nI will not call. \nI will use the app that now seems to be working. \nIf I have further problems, I will return the device and will not waste my time re-engaging with the unhelpful Alexa help desk. \nIt’s too bad the service is so bad since my family was initially enjoying the Echo/Alexa products.', 'ArtCanadian', 'iTunes', 1, 'Impossible to login/Unhelpful Help', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-11 11:37:39'),
	(446, 'I noticed the last couple of days I had to re link my SiriusXM account , it was fine before . Not sure if it had to do with the last update', 'Jeffmoney', 'iTunes', 2, 'Not saving link more than a day', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-11 12:11:08'),
	(447, 'Pointless and waist of money, guess only developer gives 5 stars , so sad , better return this crap , it’s not worth a penny , even then I wouldn’t buy it ,', 'Zeroidkv', 'iTunes', 1, 'Loll', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-11 19:37:52'),
	(448, 'Can’t connect Alexa to the internet. The app is unresponsive and the app format is not helpful.', 'Husker Red Hand', 'iTunes', 1, 'Wanky', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-11 20:03:22'),
	(449, 'The recent update for this app has it even more infuriating and useless than before. I am not able to connect Echo to my phone or to the network anymore because half of the app doesn’t work. I can no longer access the help and feedback section as well as the settings. It’s beginning to be more inconvenient using this app than just manually doing things yourself.', 'HyperPumaNova24', 'iTunes', 1, 'Currently Garbage', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-11 23:41:07'),
	(450, 'Locks up a lot.', 'sjellison', 'iTunes', 3, 'Eh', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 01:47:32'),
	(451, 'Everything else about Amazon is easily, intuitive and user friendly... except this app. You wouldn’t think it would be that hard. It just needs to have a search function, actually show the music that’s playing on the player screen, etc.', 'Cu2 bugger', 'iTunes', 2, 'Disappointing', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 03:25:14'),
	(452, 'The app constantly crashes. I can\'t get in to the settings.', 'Iil l', 'iTunes', 1, 'Awful', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 04:37:19'),
	(453, 'My last name is "required" now! why?!', '@Sigil', 'iTunes', 1, 'App and service just keeps getting worse.. (like Apple)', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 06:03:14'),
	(454, 'If Amazon manages to make this application any slower, particularly when trying to simply change the time on an alarm, they will have achieved the impossible.', 'Inspiration frog', 'iTunes', 2, 'Award for Slowest Application', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 08:27:32');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(455, 'This app STILL continues to devolve. Freezes constantly, can’t even set the darn alarm, and that’s basically the whole point of the 150 dollar egg timer I bought to go along with this crapp.\n\nI am beyond floored at how non-functional this trashware is, and about how little amazon apparently thinks of its customers. \n\nThere is NO EXCUSE for this kind of poor programming.', 'tataguy00', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible - Updated for 2018', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 12:21:04'),
	(456, 'User interface for volume control on the app seems kluge. I’d like to see more precision and improved visuals indicating volume. Right now, label for volume setting (number) is blocked by user’s finger when adjusting. Also, app indicates there are only 10 discrete volume levels. However, I can achieve many more when adjusting the volume manually on my echo unit. Please offer more fine tuning of volume on the app.', 'Mobjack447', 'iTunes', 2, 'Room for Improvement', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-12 18:50:20'),
	(457, 'I have to say the amozon elexa was ok but now it is awesome they had a huge update and I have to say in my opinion it is better than then Google home', 'Jac85jac06', 'iTunes', 5, 'Outstanding', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 01:13:53'),
	(458, 'I can no longer control amazon music with this app! What happened ??!!', 'Master K!', 'iTunes', 2, 'What happened to music controls?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 01:56:33'),
	(459, 'I bought 3 Insignia smart plugs from Best Buy. I returned them all and tried to remove them from the app. Every time I rediscovered devices, those removed plugs popped up again from nowhere. One star for an app created by such a big company like Amazon.', 'HungDoan82', 'iTunes', 1, 'Buggy App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 04:09:32'),
	(460, 'I expect better from Amazon.', 'Alexs112', 'iTunes', 1, 'Great product, horrible app.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 06:22:51'),
	(461, 'Can you guys change the volume control from a slider to something with incremental buttons, please?! I like to play soft music to go to sleep, but then I open the app to adjust the volume and if I try to just turn it a tiny bit down, it goes all the way down. Then I try to turn it a little up and it goes all the way up. It’s ridiculously frustrating.', 'aloreep', 'iTunes', 2, 'Frustrating', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 09:29:34'),
	(462, 'Would be nice if I could actually log into the app. When I enter my credentials the app first asks for a captcha, then when I enter it a second time it just resets', 'tanman2277', 'iTunes', 1, 'Can’t log in', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 14:41:53'),
	(463, 'While a good idea, I find this app very buggy, with numerous lag times and freezes.  Amazon can do better!', 'SoldinSeattle', 'iTunes', 2, 'Buggy!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 17:55:29'),
	(464, 'Amazon please fix this buggy app!!! When I first downloaded it I had no issues and now I can barely do anything in the app because it is constantly freezing!! I bought 7 Echo devices for my home for Christmas and now I am very frustrated as I cannot set them up in the app because it just freezes. I am a huge Amazon fan. Please fix!!', 'ER Sierra', 'iTunes', 1, 'Please fix the bugs!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 18:55:41'),
	(465, 'Can\'t just say "Alexa thumbs down on this song" because apparently you now have to do that from your station list?! What?! This was never an issue before. Also the UI is not good at all, not to mention on the echo dot Alexa knows only 2% of what she is asked, great if you want to ask her the weather and a few other small insignificant things but overall this app is not that good and it\'s stupid updates make it worse', 'AppleHasNoInnovationAtAll', 'iTunes', 1, 'No more thumbs down on a song', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 19:15:18'),
	(466, 'The Alex platform is amazing. This app is terrible and seems to get worse with every update. \n\nStill no support for my X.', 'cameronrye', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 19:39:53'),
	(467, 'Is this from official amazon?', 'Ochie Jones', 'iTunes', 4, 'Official?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 21:57:28');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(468, 'At first the app worked great, but after a few weeks of use the app freezes on my phone. I uninstalled and reinstalled and now it works fine but I’m wondering when it will freeze up again. Also I’m not getting what I want from my flash briefing, it keeps giving me news from sources I don’t use and none from the news sources I do use.', 'alwaysrosy2', 'iTunes', 3, 'Not sure yet', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 21:57:11'),
	(469, 'The app hasn\'t been Updated for iPhone X. Also, the app is not designed very well.', 'estoughton', 'iTunes', 1, 'Not Updated for iPhone X', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-13 23:22:35'),
	(470, 'Echo’s are awesome but this app is absolutely terrible. I wish Amazon would put a little more time, effort and money into making this a usable app.', 'brettdevon', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 00:35:23'),
	(471, 'The app has some great features and would be great if it worked flawlessly. I have to wait 5-10 seconds between actions or it will freeze. I constantly have to kill it and then take it slower to keep it from freezing. Very disappointing.', 'Bobdavid7206', 'iTunes', 3, 'Needs Fixing', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 02:08:03'),
	(472, 'This app is so infuriatingly slow. It takes about 5 minutes to load every time I open it and, when I try to provide feedback (of which I have a lot re: Alexa’s various incapabilities) it slows down my keyboard down to the point where I cannot type anything.\n\nAt this point, I do my best to avoid using the app, but from what I remember when I did use it, it was unintuitive to navigate and the features were disappointing. I’m considering returning all my Echo devices and looking for a product that allows for better control from my iPhone, not to mention an ability to actually look up useful information, which Alexa doesn’t seem to be able to do.', 'Jgv0814', 'iTunes', 1, 'Borderline useless', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 04:51:53'),
	(473, 'Pretty tired of having to re-link my serious XM application to my Dot every day. It gets worse with each update.', 'BEAGLEMUSIC', 'iTunes', 2, 'Linking every day', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 05:22:27'),
	(474, 'Guys please please please adjust how the volume control functions. When you tap on the speaker icon to activate volume adjustment you currently have users having to slide there finger up and down. While a user does this we can not see the numbers indicating a change in volume. You should change it to going from left to right and have the numbers pop up above the users finger or stylist. Currently it is not very smooth user experience. Sort of a bummer when it comes to that category. But other than that app is pretty solid.', 'ralphenit88', 'iTunes', 2, 'Change volume control for in App', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 09:06:19'),
	(475, 'So confusing. Why default to messenger? I’m lost on all the skills I could/should enable and they are difficult to find. Not listed in an orderly fashion on app.', 'Tojagi', 'iTunes', 3, 'App not user friendly', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 11:14:29'),
	(476, 'I was able to use the Alexa app until the latest update, but now nothing appears on the screen. For those of us who use voiceover, this app is completely useless… Please fix this glitch!', 'inaccessible Alexa', 'iTunes', 1, 'Latest update not good for voiceover users', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 14:55:28'),
	(477, 'I bought my Alexa mostly to manage my shopping and to do list, and have found it to be terribly feature-lacking:\n-app takes over 1 minute to start\n-app tries to force you to authorize extra permissions before letting you use it\n-the list shown on my phone omits items on my list in the browser\n-can’t modify or remove items using he echo; need to use the app\n-doesn’t check if an item is already on the list when you add it (I don’t need milk 8 times on the list)\n\nAmazon ignores any feedback for basic improvements that would fix any one of these issues.', 'MehCity', 'iTunes', 2, 'Overrated', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 16:24:57'),
	(478, 'I have a new iPhone, and every time this app updates I have to re-allow permissions, which never works. I then have to delete the app and reinstall. Total pain! The app itself is ok, but needs to be more user friendly.', 'Bokloepfer', 'iTunes', 2, 'Have to reinstall with each update', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 16:59:52');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(479, 'Shopping list is buggy and unresponsive', 'Tristn2', 'iTunes', 1, 'Shopping list is buggy and unresponsive', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 17:42:20'),
	(480, 'When starting the app won’t get pass permissions page. So it’s useless at least on iPhone 10', '@Ndrea1818', 'iTunes', 1, 'Won’t get pass permissions', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 18:32:35'),
	(481, '@Developers:\nThe ONLY reason I ever open this app is to look at my grocery list at the store. \nThat requires minimum 3 clicks to get to every time I open the app, regardless of which route I take to get to it. \nSeriously, if I click on any part of a item in my feed that shows something I added to my list, other than the text of the item, I expect to be brought to the list. Not a drop down showing options of what to do with the item, not a list of all my lists, just the list.\nIf you are going to have a dedicated task bar along the bottom, one of the buttons should take me to my most recently viewed list items. As it is, the current three are completely useless to me. \nFURTHERMORE, if I am changing the name of an item on my list, and hit DONE or click away, I expect my typing so far to be SAVED, not discarded. \nA. Who do you have designing the interface, and B. can I have their job?', 'Ruuyn', 'iTunes', 2, 'Lists are frustrating', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 21:03:26'),
	(482, 'Who is in charge of approving this updates? The volume feature in the alexa app is horrible. Very difficult to change from 1 to 2 to 3. Because of this I barely use this app.', 'dannymaverick', 'iTunes', 2, 'Volume button', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-14 21:27:45'),
	(483, 'App offers only a fraction of the tools you need to control Alexa. Needs force touch functions to allow direct voice input without opening the app.  Needs a widget on the lock screen. Would also be nice to access smart home accessories from force touch.  I suspect the inclusion of any of these things would result in less need for echo devices, so it makes sense that the app is bare bones.', 'Dub', 'iTunes', 2, 'Only a fraction as useful as Alexa', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-15 11:10:42'),
	(484, 'At first, the echo did pretty much everything we asked. But now I say the start phrase that it *gives* me on the app, and it can’t help me with that. Or, I want to go on the app to say that the last thing I said wasn’t understood, or to repeat what I did earlier, and it’s not all present, even in the history. Literally have never written a review. A 4am Alexa shouting at me that she “can’t help me” with sleep sounds is enough to make me write one.', 'caitb46', 'iTunes', 2, 'More and more frustrating', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-15 11:12:26'),
	(485, 'I can’t complain, app does what I need it to do. Would like an update to support the iPhone X screen though.', 'Valentino Vuitton', 'iTunes', 4, 'Works good', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-15 11:46:37'),
	(486, 'This app needs a lot of help and further development. I bought it with my Sonos one and it will not properly work my speakers. It does not know the difference between bedroom speakers living room speakers kitchen speakers etc. I love the idea of using my Sonos with voice control however I’m very disappointed. Please fix this app I’ve already made the investment.', 'JRporter', 'iTunes', 1, 'Doesn’t work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-15 13:30:06'),
	(487, 'This doesn\'t work! Alexa doesn\'t even speak and its so hard to control and plus you\'re copying siri and google home mini and hey google!!!! Just stoppppp', 'its annoying and boring', 'iTunes', 1, 'Dowsnt even work', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-15 16:00:37'),
	(488, 'Whenever I️ go onto the app I️t is stuck on a screen that says “Give Alexa Permissions.” I️ can’t get off of this screen therefore I️ can’t use the app. Needs fixing. Thanks', 'Ryan Tomblin', 'iTunes', 1, 'Glitch?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-16 01:42:33'),
	(489, 'Please make this app support the iPhone X', 'alecminichini', 'iTunes', 1, 'WHY DOESNT THIS APP SUPPORT THE IPHONE X?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-16 03:28:06'),
	(490, 'For some reason, the app will randomly forget the account login. Once you login again it wants to perform setup. The setup process gets stuck at for first request to “allow” access.\n\nOnly option is to delete app and start all over again.', 'Humptybump', 'iTunes', 1, 'forgets login and settings', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-16 10:25:01');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(491, 'Now if this app could be a so called hybrid between the other smart devices with what it can already do that be awesome but lately the app crashes after getting into any other categories or even the settings. Wish it wouldn’t happen.', 'Bassin guy', 'iTunes', 4, 'Apps really good but', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-16 10:26:46'),
	(492, 'Love Alexa but this app has a long way to go. Please fix! Most of the time doesn’t load and opens to blank white screen. Given up on shopping list. I basically keep this app just to set up Alexa.', 'Notorious Nator', 'iTunes', 1, 'Doesn’t load, like EVER', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-16 15:45:25'),
	(493, 'This happens to be one of the worst apps to use. There is almost no control over your devices. You can’t access them without having to go in and out of the app bumpers times.', 'Dev8tor', 'iTunes', 1, 'The worst app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 00:53:20'),
	(494, 'Alexa works great, however the app gives me a blank home screen.', 'HJS93', 'iTunes', 2, 'Home screen not loading', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 01:49:34'),
	(495, 'I love my Amazon Echoes (multiple) which I use daily but I would suggest an update to the app interface with a more eye appealing and user friendly condensed version without needing to scroll. My biggest desire (Alexa are you listening?!) is an added feature that utilizes Apple’s 3D Touch. For instance, a firm press could immediately link you to your shopping list or to-dos. Overall it’s a great product!', 'ChrisMez', 'iTunes', 5, 'Alexa are you listening?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 02:26:17'),
	(496, 'The app just feels like a bad front end User interface that connects to a laggy back end web interface. Amazon is an amazing company your app team needs to do better.', 'Bempah', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa=great product / Alexa App=not so great', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 04:11:35'),
	(497, 'If I can’t think of the perfect thing to ask my Echo to play, I’d like to use the app to scroll through Amazon Music...but good luck finding anything. This app is a disorganized mess.', 'WhalesTales', 'iTunes', 1, 'Terrible for music.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 04:46:39'),
	(498, 'Stuck on some setup screen and theres no exit button only later and allow. i reset the app and my phone', 'Sc@m', 'iTunes', 1, 'broken', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 09:39:35'),
	(499, 'Cannot grant permissions. Pressing allow does nothing. Also Alexa voice recognition continues to get worse. This app on the iPhone X and ios 11 is useless and does not work.', 'The PUA Switch', 'iTunes', 1, 'Cannot Give Permissions', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-17 20:02:01'),
	(500, 'Since your new update I can\'t add anything to a shopping list or to do list from my  Galaxy S7', 'George Conklin', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-23 00:00:00'),
