	(611, 'New updated app does not work unless you set up calling, which I do not want at this time.  When I try to skip this step, the app stops working.  I\'ve had to uninstall and I\'m using and older version of the app on another device to control Alexa because this update removed the old app from my phone.  Amazon and Alexa are great, but this update is terrible. Please fix this, Amazon!', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-27 00:00:00'),
	(612, 'Since the last update, it is slow to load... and I don\'t want my home screen to be conversations and bs.  This new update us frustrating and I want to throw it out the window.', 'Christina Phillips', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-27 00:00:00'),
	(613, 'The app won\'t open, \'ALEXA\' please get the old app back', 'William Bower', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-27 00:00:00'),
	(614, 'Update: May 25 update made it worse. Now there\'s a nag message I can\'t  a make go away, wanting me to set up voice calling. NO! Nothing else fixed. Original: This version is seriously effed. Seriously. No longer works in landscape mode on any of my Android devices (or iOS, for the record). "Now playing" is no longer a selection in the hamburger menu. Volume control slider is no longer persistent on the "Now playing" screen. You have  to press the speaker icon to make it appear, and it goes away too quickly. Stupid UI choices all around.', 'Tom Betz', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-27 00:00:00'),
