	(638, 'The calling features sucks! You can only communicate with other people who have the Alexa device or app. Basically the calling feature is useless.', 'Cinnamonsage J M', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-28 00:00:00'),
	(639, 'The app won\'t even load anymore since the new update.', 'Evan Horsley', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-28 00:00:00'),
	(640, 'The computer age for me is admittedly one or two generations younger than I am. So, even though I can\'t possibly comprehend all the potential within this app, the sheer fascination with it earns the highest rating I can give. The consistent problem I have is the avalanche of research necessary to plod through learning how to use it. Normally I would give a lower rating because of the mandated learning curve. Yet, everything we have been able to apply has not only been useful, but fun. Consider this: when I was a kid, my parents sometimes still read by candle light. True story. Echo is near magic to me right alongside being able to talk with someone through a hand held communicator and computers that talk. Those things would never be real, right?', 'Sam Stone', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-05-28 00:00:00'),
