	(785, 'After the last update this app stopped working on my galaxy s7. Any ways to fix this?', 'Svitlana Elsbernd', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-02 00:00:00'),
	(786, 'When my app would not get past the wifi setup, I disabled the \'auto network switch\' feature on my phone. Go into the wifi settings and you will find it there. I have a Samsung Note 5, the process will vary based on make and model of your phone. Once I disabled the auto network switch feature I was able to complete all setup procedures. I hope this helps someone as I was on the verge of sending mine back...', 'chris muller', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-02 00:00:00'),
	(787, 'Takes forever to start.', 'Clora Lee-Kwong', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-02 00:00:00'),
	(788, 'No networks available. Please connect and try again. 💢', 'steven pavelish', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-02 00:00:00'),
	(789, 'Easy to set up with a tablet.  Calls and messaging setup comes with the app being on a cellphone or tablet with call and messaging features. Skills setup was slightly challenging in the absence of printed instructions in the box with the Dot.  I had all of my smart plug connected devices enabled and controlled by Alexa in about 10 minutes. I did have to change abbreviated names to full names for Alexa to recognize and complete commands. I am impressed with the limited use I have employed so far. My next test will be disconnecting power and reconnecting to determine if there is continuity with the setup and connection to Amazon echo services since I do not intend to have my DOT connected 24/7 for privacy considerations.', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 4, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-02 00:00:00'),
	(790, 'Loved it before the update. Now it\'s very slow and can only be viewed in portrait. Phone use primarily. Tablets are not dead...', 'gerald mcwhorter', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-03 00:00:00'),
	(791, 'Can\'t connect to my WiFi have spent all day up loading this bloody app 8 times and it still doesn\'t work', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-03 00:00:00'),
	(792, 'The app doesn\'t work at all since the last update. Unable to pair Dot with wifi which in turn makes the Dot useless. Shall I now request money back for the all the Dots, if there is no way of making them work without the app...?', 'David Kristek', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-03 00:00:00'),
	(793, 'Works fine if you enable and update audible...', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-03 00:00:00'),
	(794, 'The set up was a pain.  Not so easy, took me a day to figure it out.  Kept getting a blank  white screen while trying to get the wi-fi connected.  I tried both my Samsung Glaxey7 and Ipad...finally a message poped up on my phone ap that said to enable auto wi-fi networks? After playing with the settings and pushing every network button, I guess I finally got the right button.  Now I am in business. Irritating to figure out.  So we will see how Alexa does from here.', 'Charlene Highsaw', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-06-03 00:00:00'),
