	(1991, 'Love  it', 'Lucy Guzman', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-01 00:00:00'),
	(1992, '--Update for calling causes app to crash constantly. After installing it looks like it will open and work properly, but when it gets to the step where it requires you to pick your name from a list, it crashes. I can\'t skip the voice set up, but attempting to complete it crashes the app every time. I\'ve uninstalled and reinstalled a half dozen times to fix it - not only is it wasting my time, it\'s making my $500 in Alexa devices significantly less useful. Completely flipping worthless update - don\'t risk it til the bugs are repaired.--  Update: the bugs are repaired. Voice calling works seamlessly between my phone and all of my Alexa devices. I only wish the app had better control settings for IOT devices.', 'Melanie F.', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-02 00:00:00'),
	(1993, 'amazing', 'Gabriella Mattoni', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-02 00:00:00'),
	(1994, 'Useless for me. Bought to control my Dish Hopper 3. Worked in a very limited sense for a few days, now does nothing. Either responds with "not sure how to help you with that", or LEDs just spin and then nothing happens. Can\'t pause the Hopper, can\'t tune to a channel or anything else. Just another piece of "shelfware" now.  Update: Now appears each time Alexa app updates, Dish skill quits working and must be in/reinstalled.  Dish skill also needs to be smarter and more flexible, but I assume that\'s on Dish to do. Updatingto 2 stars.', 'Philip Hershey', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-02 00:00:00'),
