	(2064, 'The app disconnects my wifi causing my data to be used at an alarming rate. Not the Echo, the app. This app. Without the app being installed on my Galaxy 7, I can use my Amazon Echo, play music, enable skills, etc and as long as I\'m connected to my wifi I use NO data. But when I install this app, and even if I am not using the Echo, my data allowance begins to burn away rapidly.  When I put my phone down & my screen times out, my wifi gets disconnected.  When I use my phone and open the screen, I see a popup telling my my wifi has been connected... meaning it was disconnected during the phones down time. I have searched but cannot find a setting within the app that may stop this. So, I cannot keep it installed.  If there is a fix gor this please let me know. Sent from my Samsung Galaxy S7.', 'Russell', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-07 00:00:00'),
