	(2302, 'I can forgive the errors on the voice recognition on echo as it\'s relatively new but the app is shockingly poor. It offers friends to type in so you can customise your settings but the ok or submit buttons are never enabled so you have no way of customising it at all. One of the most basic requirements of an app and it doesn\'t work!', 'Catherine Hankin', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-29 00:00:00'),
	(2303, 'When will the drop in feature come to the UK?', 'Craig Kearney', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-29 00:00:00'),
	(2304, 'This app is quite bad. It\'s unconscionably slow. Initial load times are slow. Opening the now playing is slow. Everything takes ages, are we sure it\'s 2017 and I\'m on a high end device?  Additionally, functionality is not what it should be. Why is playing Amazon\'s own music service so hard? Sometimes Alexa doesn\'t understand me and I want to play a specific song or album from Amazon Music Unlimited - you can\'t, apparently it\'s just radio and popular. What on Earth and I paying for this service for then? Spotify gives you full control of Alexa music from the app.   Also while the new whole home audio festure is welcome, it\'s still lacking. I need to be able to submit a device into multiple groups. I have five echos. Maybe I want a group for my upstairs echos, my downstairs echos, and a whole home option? Can\'t do that. Silly.', 'Mark Davis', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-08-29 00:00:00'),
