	(3390, 'Can\'t search for music...', 'Luiz Carvalho', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00'),
	(3391, 'The old skills that I had from the states can not be erased because now its starting in Canada. They need to give an option for removing all the skills.', 'Francisco J. Sanchez Careaga', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00'),
	(3392, 'Good for many things but lists on a 3g connection while shopping are ridiculously slow. Sometimes they won\'t even load. Lists are just text. 8 bits / ascii character, so this is a crazy flaw.', 'Bill Barowy', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00'),
	(3393, 'I love my dot. Fitted my car.', 'ARUNN P.M.KUMAR', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00'),
	(3394, 'If I could give this app a negative review I would. I\'m not a huge fan of my dot to begin with but the app just destroys any positive feelings I might have had.   One of the biggest things I use the app for is text to speech on my Kindle books. Not only can I not arrange how I want the icons to look or hide services I don\'t use, but I can\'t   search through my books for the title I want or sort them. It is also virtually impossible to just say "Alexa read XXXXX" because she has no idea what I\'m talking about.  My roommate foumd the same thing when she tried to get the app to read to her. You have to dig through all the books to find the one you want and then hit play.   Also, Alexa is extremely  spotty with pronunciation (i.e., a character whose name is Manny sometimes gets called Man, sometimes pronounced Many and sometimes pronounced Manny; a character named Colin is sometimes prounced like Cawlin and sometimes like Colon).  All that being said, the biggest thing I hate about the app is that it randomly stops, as if a sleep timer went off and it stops reading. If I wake her up by saying "Alexa", she reads a few more words and then stops or she will randomly start reading again (i.e., a 3 am the book will come back on for a sentence or two and then will stop again). This would continue the whole book if I let it. Amazon says it\'s most likely the internet connection but I can tell you it absolutely is not.   I realize Alexa was a pioneer in AI in her early days, but one would think Amazon would have improved her since then. Not so much.', 'Marlise Anderson', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00'),
	(3395, 'Still it\'s not supporting saavn', 'Ullas M', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00'),
	(3396, 'Seems Amazon  haven\'t  taken  this seriously.  UI is no where  near to standards  of their shopping  app.', 'Venkata Sai', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-11-19 00:00:00');
