	(3926, 'Good but need little speed up in app', 'krishnan B', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 00:00:00'),
	(3927, 'Now if we can only get Amazon to realize that BING is NOT a proper search engine and some of us want to, you know, search stuff with our voice-controlled devices. I won\'t lie, due to that extreme limitation I regret ever buying my echo devices. Google home does everything Alexa does better. The downside is my music library is mostly amazon and my Audible account. But for information or understanding things - Alexa is piss poor at best. Google Assistant wins EVERY TIME. switch out back ends and Amazon Echo devices would be my #1 choice. I used to work for M$ internal Helpdesk and Bing is so bad, we used Google to search for our troubleshooting solutions when. We needed to, then for policy sake we would Bing the search results page of Google.', 'Andy Ford', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-18 00:00:00'),
