	(4021, 'I am missing the option "music video and books" only have "Music and book"', 'vishal patel', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 00:00:00'),
	(4022, 'Lately, all of my Echo devices are constantly telling me that there was a problem executing the command or that the device lost its connection. All my other devices are connected with no issues and this happens while my FireTV is steadily streaming (and yes, I have more than enough bandwidth for multiple streams, etc). This is most frustrating. The music groups are useless because if you have your device connected to a Bluetooth speaker, it severs the connection and plays the music thru the device (which sounds horrible on a Dot). Furthermore, the Tap can\'t be added to a music group. Calling one of your other devices is interesting, but it would be more useful as an intercom without having to "answer" with a command. (I want to give my 3-year-old instructions in another room, but he can\'t answer the call) Calling another device also severs any Bluetooth connections. Alexa had a huge head start, but is quickly falling behind in useful features now that there is competition.', 'Channing Hayden III', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 00:00:00'),
	(4023, 'Awsome app works great conected to my wifi while I blinked anyone having problems needs to get out more  If Alexa was able to use Google she would be unstoppable and could easily take over the world as it is the other one that shalt not be mentioned should sit in the corner with a D on there app', 'Peter Hodson', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2017-12-22 00:00:00'),
