	(4729, 'Hi', 'Daloonlake HD', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4730, 'Prior to the recent app, it was great. There is a bug with the current app. Keeps taking me to the Settings page and I can\'t exit out unless I close the app.', 'H Laible', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4731, 'I had to uninstall and re install...app stopped working', 'Analin Guevara', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4732, 'I know there are skilled developers at Amazon but this app is not a reflection of that. Love all the technology that went into the echo dot but using this app is such a chore.  The setup is unintuitive, finicky, and I feel lucky if I can even get it to work. Put a couple quality devs on making this app great so people can enjoy their dots even more.', 'Jake Woodlee', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4733, 'So far so good. Just learning the ropes. Wish there was more of a podcast selection like Google home....', 'Tracey Marie', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4734, 'Frustrating, limited, and poorly implemented.', 'Rob Deaner', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4735, 'I thought this would be easy to use but unfortunately it took me multiple failed attempts to set up Alexa. I had to go to the website instead and now when I choose spotify as my default music library it wouldnt work. This app needs a lot of work.', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
	(4736, 'Interface is spartan but it works. Seems as of late it has been locking out some of my smart home devices which has bee frustrating to say the least. Needs more sparkle or something. The drop-in feature is ok but is in a strange spot at the top of the screen to me. It works but they did not drop a whole lot of money on the UI design I am guessing.', 'Earl Hartsell', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-06 00:00:00'),
