	(5406, 'Ok', 'MohaNanavati', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5407, 'No play button? I was hoping to use this to get my Echo to play albums that it refuses to play via voice command, but when I get to the album, I can only shuffle or play individual tracks. If there\'s a way to make it play an entire album in order, could someone please enlighten me.', 'Amanda N', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5408, 'Goooooood', 'Quadsquad', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5409, 'The playback controls stopped working, a fix on that would be nice! Thanks!', 'Tyler Workman', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5410, 'Needs work.', 'Stephen Trofimuk', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5411, 'I came on here JUST to review the new position of the volume controller. I LOVE it at the top and it seems that I can adjust my music volume much better and easier. I listen to Pandora nightly to help me relax and sleep and this Change alone was greatly appreciated!', 'caratdiamond10', 'iTunes', 5, 'The Volume on music is better positioned', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 10:16:38'),
	(5412, 'I give this app 2 stars for the vital functionality it provides to administer your Echo devices. But, it’s really a horrendously clunky app. The usability was always bad but it has gotten worse with successive updates. Not only are the aesthetics still bad, but the performance/speed is atrocious. Half of my usage is spent wondering if the pulsating 3 dots are a wait indicator or if the transaction stalled. \n\nIn sloppy updates, recent versions have made the volume control bar harder to use than before. I have to play a song to change the volume in my kids room which means if it’s up high they get blasted at night when I’m starting sleep music remotely. The volume slider is crazy hard to touch and the volume number is under my finger. \n\nSeriously, I can’t list all the bad usability in this thing but if the performance was more reliable and snappier, I could live with bad design. \n\nIn missing features, why can’t I set the music volume low and comfortable as a background setting, and get Alexa’s voice volume high so she’s not whispering to me when I ask the song name.', 'GreenJump', 'iTunes', 2, 'Disappointed!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 13:01:36'),
	(5413, 'Useless garbage. Amazon development of this app is abysmal. Eons between updates and bug fixes.', 'skiaddict', 'iTunes', 1, 'Crashing constantly.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 14:50:08'),
	(5414, 'Since the latest update, neither my husband nor I can use the app at all. It is perpetually frozen no matter how many times we restart it.', 'Cairbear816', 'iTunes', 1, 'Completely unusable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 16:00:56');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(5415, 'Alexa is more of a novelty, not much there for practical use. It would be nice if Amazon programmed Alexa to perform more routines when you say a specific command. For instance, it would play a specific type of music station (ie relaxing music or sounds) when I give a specific command (Alexa, time to get ready for bed).  Another nice feature would be to link reminders to Alexa in routines, such as when I say “Alexa, Good Morning” on a Monday, she would tell me the reminders I have programmed for Mondays. Linking a smart phone “reminder” app to Alexa, to play when a routine is created, would be fabulous!  Right now, aside from asking her to play music (most of what I listen to isn’t available on Amazon Music) and use her for my morning routine to get weather, traffic, and daily briefing, I don’t use it much.  It seems to be in an infancy stage even after a couple of years.  It could be great. I look forward to when it is.', 'PL Buckeye Girl', 'iTunes', 2, 'Not much available', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 23:33:24'),
	(5416, 'The app will not update when opened. The page stays right at the home page. Can’t get to routines, settings, anything. Not satisfied with the app or the device.', 'Fernis450', 'iTunes', 1, 'Most recent update Jan 25ish 2018.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 23:51:36'),
	(5417, 'SUGGESTION: Please provide native playback (without Bluetooth) of Apple Music and Google Music Play. I am considering to switching to Google device because of this. I understand the protectionist impulse but a successful device and platform in the long run is the one that provides access and doesn’t limit one.\n\nSUGGESTION: Search for Prime music is still not provided. Echo voice recognition is still not perfect. Why not provide search function just like Amazon Music app does?!\n\nFixed: Latest GUI change broke the volume control. It is EXTREMELY hard to slide volume control and sometimes accidentally jumps to lowest or maximum volume, risking a damage to your hearing! UPDATE: This issue is now fixed with very nice and responsive volume control. Thank you! This alone gains a whole star rating for me.', 'Arthur Dent ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯', 'iTunes', 3, 'Some bugs reported solved. Suggested further improvements', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-01 01:38:59'),
	(5418, 'I loved the dot because it allowed me to continue playing music for my dogs while away from home. A recent update took that remote ability away. Therefore there is no reason to keep Amazon prime or the dot.', 'EBowser', 'iTunes', 1, 'No longer controls music remotely', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-01 03:08:24'),
	(5419, 'I can\'t even get the app to load. All I get is a black screen.', 'Karen S.', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5420, 'Wouldn\'t link to my amazon account', 'rev myk', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5421, 'This app is getting worse and worse all the time.  wanted to do the things I asked.', 'Linda Holt', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5422, 'Doesn\'t seem to work on your phone only. Apparently you have to already have it on another device.  I guess I won\'t be trying it out after all. OK Google!', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5423, 'This is very cool helps if ur lazy', 'Sarah Guzdek', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5424, 'Don\'t need it, don\'t use it, don\'t want it. The Fire has enough memory shortages without it. But THANK YOU for adding the ability to uninstall. Seriously, thank you.', 'Dennis O\'Brien', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5425, 'Apps gd bar most of the stuff is for the USA why are most of the skills I find for USA why show for UK if only available in us', 'westley lathwood', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
	(5426, 'I could have given five star, if you at all us features in USA to Indian version and for if performance is improved.', 'Jaison Peter', 'GooglePlayStore', 4, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-01-31 00:00:00'),
