	(5625, 'Oh yeah', 'David Anderson', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5626, 'You Have Not Changed The Description Of Update Contents For At Least The Last Four Updates.  Any Chance You Could Tell Us What You Are Doing To The App?', 'sittingduck', 'iTunes', 3, 'What’s in the updates??', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 10:32:33'),
	(5627, 'The app is not well designed IMHO, so most of the time I use Bluetooth from my phone and that works great. \n\nPLEASE update the app to support the iPhone X. Even Google updated Google Voice for the iPhone X. C\'mon!!', 'Comfortably_nick', 'iTunes', 3, 'I love Alexa but it doesn\'t seem like much effort is being put in the app.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 12:23:20'),
	(5628, 'Wake up Jeff. Get some devs on this app.', 'Mitchell Pash', 'iTunes', 1, 'Developers Asleep', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 13:01:42'),
	(5629, 'Where is it? It has been months. Update for iPhone X!', 'mrmistermr', 'iTunes', 1, 'iPhone X Support?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 13:35:53'),
	(5630, 'Please make this app support the iPhone X. It just looks bad on the iPhone X screen', 'alecminichini', 'iTunes', 1, 'STILL WHY DOESNT THIS APP SUPPORT THE IPHONE X?', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 15:26:56'),
	(5631, 'This app works well for the most part but the most troubling issue I have with it is the Lists. I tell Alexa to add something to my shopping list which it does a great job of. The issue arises when I go to the store and try to remove items as I put them in my cart. So it works well when I open it for the first time but if my phone locks and I unlock it on the list again to delete something else I just put on my cart it doesn’t receive my command and the item stays on the list until I close the app and reopen it. Please fix this because I use this feature all the time and it gets cumbersome. Thanks', 'no health app sycn', 'iTunes', 3, 'Deleting List Items Issue', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 17:41:02'),
	(5632, 'App either crashes or freezes upon opening 9/10 times.', 'Pezistential', 'iTunes', 1, 'Totally unusable', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 18:21:21'),
	(5633, 'Feb 2018 review. My external blue tooth speaker will no longer work with Alexa Dot. Period! \n\nSept 2017 review-This app continues to devolve with each update. As of the latest update you now have to manually select music for your other dot or echo if you want them both to play. I keep the echo music on all day and when I shower, I stream from my dot to the shower radio. If I ask Dot alexa to play 60\'s music, she says you already have a device playing and would I rather hear it on this device. If you say yes, my echo turns off and the dot plays. Certainly Bezo\'s can hire better developers than this. \n\nI still cannot fathom the idea that the developers think this update is an improvement. It is the exact opposite. Volume control and "now playing " features are no longer static at the bottom of the screen. Latest version May 9, 2017 cripples the ability to quickly access volume control on iPhone. Can take as many as 4 steps just to get to a volume button. And the time between these steps is not "snappy", if you will. The finger slide volume control is buggy. You can\'t even see the volume number because it\'s directly under your finger tip. Pitiful pitiful implementation. App is clunky and slow to respond to touches on iPhone 6 plus. I would love to revert to the older version.', 'kenr96', 'iTunes', 2, 'warning for update Feb 2018', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 18:50:07'),
	(5634, 'It\'s glitchy and unreliable; constantly freezes. And it gets worse with every update...', 'Jgome0511', 'iTunes', 1, 'Love Alexa, hate the app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 21:23:45'),
	(5635, 'Write release notes for a better rating.', 'Provide Release Notes!', 'iTunes', 1, 'Write release notes for a better rating.', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:13:26');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(5636, 'This last update was said to make adding and controlling iHome devices easier. Well now Alexa can’t find my ihome smartplugs and says there was a problem while my devices are working fine through their app. Please fix this\n\nEdit 2/7/18 : AGAIN you put an update out & my ihome smartplugs stop working again. I have half of my house connected &  it’s quite inconvenient at this point. Thinking about just going to Google.', 'bryanvincent', 'iTunes', 3, 'IHome control update broke it', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:51:05'),
	(5637, 'Super annoying, it feels like a abandon ware.', 'rdschouw', 'iTunes', 1, 'No iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 01:20:59'),
	(5638, 'There is no way to delete an WiFi password from this app. Have to call customer service and reset device and profile for that.\n\nAnd NEVER EVER allow access to your contacts. It will import all contacts and hold onto them as a leach. Making all contacts available from echo device. Imagine mistakenly calling your boss on 5 am Sunday. And then spending half an hour with customer service to reset your profile because there is no way to selectively remove or add contacts. \n\nSuch a waste of the “artificial intelligence”.', 'GigBite', 'iTunes', 1, 'Intrusive app', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 01:53:00'),
	(5639, 'Amazon - love Alexa but your iOS app needs help. It keeps on crashing!', 'paddlegirl621', 'iTunes', 1, 'Keeps on crashing', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 02:15:54'),
	(5640, 'Recent changes (apparently to Alexa app) have broken the integration with iHome smart plugs.  My home is a combination of Hue and Smart Plug devices and Alexa (via 2 Echos and several Dots strategically located) is at the heart of my interactive control.  I rely on these devices being able to seamlessly be controlled via my Amazon AI helpers.  I can cover with Siri in the meantime - she still has full control, but I would like Alexa back on the job to make this all work!', 'thesingingalpaca', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa can no longer control iHome devices', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 02:43:55'),
	(5641, 'Went to look for the history of what I played on my echo dot and it disappeared with the update-good grief. And Alexa misses over Half is the commands anyway. Disappointed!', 'Marijat', 'iTunes', 2, 'It was good when I started..', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 04:00:30'),
	(5642, 'Lost all my devices on both my Android and Mac apps. Had to reset everything and now both apps are stuck on the "short video" screen. Won\'t play the video and I can get out of it. So basically the app is now useless.', 'BeachLion', 'iTunes', 2, 'Latest update crashed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 06:01:10'),
	(5643, 'The app is bad and isn’t even updated for iPhone X', 'estoughton', 'iTunes', 1, 'App is bad', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 08:04:16'),
	(5644, 'Back to 5 start now all home automation hardware is back working as it should do', 'Mark M', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5645, 'This is wonderful! So easy to install and has step by step instructions and I am stupid when it comes to this stuff! Easy!', 'Cheryl Maurer', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5646, 'Garbage', 'Steve H', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5647, 'I can\'t find my conversation icon anymore on update it\'s very frustrating   * update * I had to uninstall and reinstall the app to get it back', 'Andrea Clouden', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5648, 'Love the Dot. Unfortunately, this app won\'t install on my LG X Power. Gives a 505 error code.', 'Lyndon Dees', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5649, 'Use \'VEARN\' App Enterr (DCVG) to Start Earning So far so good.Fun way to get money. Won\'t make you rich but the extra cash is helpful. It\'s also the best exchange rate on points. McEarn points equals Mc instead of like some of the others where it takes VEarn points to reach Vc etc....Also, Use \'TOYOCASH\' App Enterr (RRED) very reliable in paying you when you redeem to toyocash. You can choose assorted giftcards as payment or transfer to WaIet for cash. Your choice. I love these guys thanks for addingsome fun to my day.', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(5650, 'No alexa voice control through the app on canada? What were you thinking. I pay for prime like everyone else update ASAP', 'Dale BIGD', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5651, 'I just activated this out of my tablet because it\'s not working well and I understand why. I have other items and I have also delete it out other things I don\'t know what\'s going on with with this appAlexa', 'Brina Green', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-07 00:00:00'),
	(5652, 'Great app. Though, I tried to create a "Goodnight" routine for my Phillips Hue bulbs. Didn\'t work and process was wonky. To dim, do I "turn off" or "turn on" bulbs to 1% brightness? I don\'t know...Didn\'t make sense to me. Anyway, it wouldn\'t dim the bulbs properly. But I\'m enjoying this echo dot device/app.', 'Kyle Parker', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5653, 'App freezes constantly and is difficult to navigate', 'Amy Rogers', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5654, 'It says buying not supported in your location', 'Premnath', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5655, 'The alarm section of this app is horrible.  Sometimes I wake up early for work ok my own and want to silently disable my alarm as to not wake my girlfriend up.  Most of the time I\'m not successful and inadvertently set an earlier alarm.  There is no joke a 60-90 second delay.    Another thing that might be related: Only the last 10 alarms should be kept.  I used to work shift work so I have quite a few alarms (possibly 100+).  If this is fixed I would give this app 5 stars.', 'Robert J', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5656, 'The Wi-Fi tutorial worked once or twice but now it\'s useless', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5657, 'Amazon best way to connect with your echo', 'Orlando Anselmetti', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5658, 'Good', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5659, 'Not working on Android Oreo...', 'Razique Anjum', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5660, 'Best', 'Elidae Dawn', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5661, 'The Alexa app in combination with different smart devices has changed the way my sister is able to live. She loves everything that allows her to do anything that anyone else can do. From voice activated plug ins and thermostat to the fire tv. After being intubated my sisters voice is neither strong nor clear yet Alexa understands her most of the time. Because of this sometimes she has to repeat herself. Alexa can be loud and my sister has a roommate so sometimes especially at night my sister wants to be able to control the smart devices from the Alexa/Amazon.com website via a specialized computer in order to not disturb her roommate. This one limitation is huge considering Alexa has no silent mode rendering Alexa useless at night for my sister.', 'finkleienhorn', 'iTunes', 4, 'Quadriplegics', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 16:58:16'),
	(5662, 'My amazon dot cannot control my yeelight even retried entire setup and still doesn’t work', 'JonnySullivan', 'iTunes', 2, 'Issues with yeelight', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 18:03:30'),
	(5663, 'Worst App ever created. Difficult to maneuver. And I can’t change my home address (Alexa somehow thinks I live 20 miles away) the app just closes the window right after I open it to change it. And to make matters worse, my first 5 questions confuse her. Also when I get calls and texts it plays the sound through the Echo Dot and NOT my phone, WOW I AM FRUSTRATED. Guess we’ll have to wait another 10 years for this whole robot/smart home thing to really kick off. Until then, this is just a waste of $40', 'Ryane5150', 'iTunes', 1, 'Wow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 20:09:00'),
	(5664, 'This app is ridiculously hard to use. All I want to do is add my fiancé’s Spotify account and it is literally impossible. On top of that, it now crashes every time I open it. How hard could it possibly be to make a companion app that lets you play music?', 'MattyMurda', 'iTunes', 1, 'Garbage', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 20:43:03');
