	(5665, 'All the money amazon invests in a bunch of crap; they can’t update the app to have iPhone X support. Stupid.', 'Beersnf928372', 'iTunes', 2, 'No iPhone X support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 21:38:17'),
	(5666, 'what did you outrageously stupid idiots do to this app?  I can no longer choose a station to play on my Dot!!  Are you morons trying to pull an Apple trick on us?  Now when I try to control my dot the app claims I cannot control my dot in any way from this insulting app.  Amazon you need to fire these children who are now writing your apps.  They must have found their software"degrees" in a box of Cracker Jacks!!!', 'Prophotoman', 'iTunes', 1, 'USELESS!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 22:47:25'),
	(5667, 'Not loading. Didn’t do anything when it did. Maybe pay some attention to this department?', 'tomofpittsburgh', 'iTunes', 1, 'Not', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 01:36:13'),
	(5668, '1- This app is very poorly designed.  Why can’t it just be like the amazon music app where I can access all of my music?  I really wish Alexa had blue tooth capability so that I can simply just stream my music. \n\n2- I would say about 50% of the time it just doesn’t respond at all when I try to click on something.   \n\nI’m just going to stick to using a blue tooth speaker where I can simply play MY music.  It’s just too simple to pass up.  I’m not always in the mood to argue with a computer voice.', 'Jen54', 'iTunes', 1, 'Mostly unresponsive and poorly designed', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 02:12:31'),
	(5669, 'Well I have a firetv. Sad to see that that is not supported even though the TV says to download this app.', 'Angela Brintzenhofe', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5670, 'Very useful and cool', 'Emil Wojcik', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5671, 'The app is supposed to have music, video and books under settings but I only have music and books, no video. I want to link my echo dot to my fire TV stick.', 'Ak Goyal', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5672, 'Slow application, Alexa voice recognition is not even in the same league as google', 'Thomas Hunter', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5673, 'EPIC AND IT WORKS', 'VersedRhyme41 Bowser', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5674, 'I love Amazon alexa but I have one question. How do i do the Gorden Ramsey thing?', 'Caleb Dobias 2', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5675, 'The Alexa devices are great.  Able to play music thruout home using setup of group.  Very cool.  Friends for dinner went home and bought an Echo.  One device at a time until comfortable speaking to an inanimate person,  Alexa.  Saying thank you n such!  Hahaha!', 'Kathleen M. Palmer', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5676, 'Cortana, Siri are way better', 'Colton Wilson', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5677, 'I just wanted to make a suggestion. I personally think that the app and echo are great. But I was bothered by the fact that you can\'t answer phone calls from friends and family who are using their mobile phone. I just wanted you to please consider this.  Thanks-Felix', 'Felix J', 'GooglePlayStore', 4, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5678, 'Smart home function not working since update. I have the smartlife app and a bunch of bulbs. Since the alexa app update the connection between the apps is intermittent at best. Sometimes IFTTT works but for some reason Alexa says she has actioned voice commands but nothing happens. Please sort this out Amazon - everything worked brilliantly until you updated.', 'Claire Hoath', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-08 00:00:00'),
	(5679, 'Need Alexa calling in India', 'Mersa Jose', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 00:00:00'),
	(5680, 'i love alexa whats there not to love?', 'michelle grooms', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 00:00:00'),
	(5681, 'I don\'t want Alexa on my device I should be able to uninstall it fully if I could give 0 stars I would I got this kindle for games only I\'ve got an iPhone which I love', 'englishdragon88', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `rating` (`id`, `review`, `author`, `review_source`, `rating`, `title`, `product_name`, `reviewed_date`) VALUES
	(5682, 'Music does not play on all echo devices at one time but transfers the music from one device to another... not a lot of video apps like crunchyroll, hulu, netflix and other major movie streaming skills.. over all my echo devices are working nearly as perfect as i intended', 'guitarmaster1900', 'iTunes', 4, 'Not bad, couple of problems', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 12:17:05'),
	(5683, 'Feb 2018 review. My external blue tooth speaker will no longer work with Alexa Dot. Period! It took some figuring out but now, instead of turning on Alexa music, then my blue tooth shower radio and instantly hearing music, I have to go into settings, blue tooth, and manually connect my external speaker each time. Add to that the fact that “recent” music stations rarely work now. I have to go directly to the Tunein option and start music from there. And the downhill slide continues. \n\nSept 2017 review-This app continues to devolve with each update. As of the latest update you now have to manually select music for your other dot or echo if you want them both to play. I keep the echo music on all day and when I shower, I stream from my dot to the shower radio. If I ask Dot alexa to play 60\'s music, she says you already have a device playing and would I rather hear it on this device. If you say yes, my echo turns off and the dot plays. Certainly Bezo\'s can hire better developers than this. \n\nI still cannot fathom the idea that the developers think this update is an improvement. It is the exact opposite. Volume control and "now playing " features are no longer static at the bottom of the screen. Latest version May 9, 2017 cripples the ability to quickly access volume control on iPhone. Can take as many as 4 steps just to get to a volume button. And the time between these steps is not "snappy", if you will. The finger slide volume control is buggy. You can\'t even see the volume number because it\'s directly under your finger tip. Pitiful pitiful implementation. App is clunky and slow to respond to touches on iPhone 6 plus. I would love to revert to the older version.', 'kenr96', 'iTunes', 2, 'warning for update Feb 2018', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 12:18:42'),
	(5684, 'Just updated and can no longer use app unless I set it up to make phone calls. I NEVER want to make calls using Alexa. So how about adding a skip option so I can use the rest of the app features? This might force me to replace Alexa with Google\'s offering.\n\nWas hoping the last update would have added a skip option. Since it didn\'t, I am going to be skipping my Prime membership. Will not be renewing.\n\nTried latest update hoping it would have a skip feature but sadly, no.\n\nThe update prior to Feb 5, 2018 update did include a skip option. So, good enough for me. I will not be installing the Feb 5 update because I fear what it might do. Will monitors reviews before I take that plunge.\n\nThanks for the SKIP. Appreciate that.', 'Pcestmoi', 'iTunes', 3, 'Update made it useless (yet again)', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 15:16:56'),
	(5685, 'I love my Alexa but every time I select the app it asks for my password. Why doesn\'t it remember it??? Nothing more annoying than passwords 😡 and this is extremely annoying! Please fix it 😩\n\nWhen I check my shopping list and then want to check my to do list it shows 2 items but then I choose my shopping list and then go back my to do list says no items. What’s going on???', 'Pabloguru', 'iTunes', 2, 'Annoying!!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 15:54:43'),
	(5686, 'Why is this thing so incredibly slow to start??? I use my echo less for certain tasks  (lists, todo) because of how painfully slow this app is', 'Ggtjhkbgfdxcjyf', 'iTunes', 2, 'So slow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 03:32:50'),
	(5687, 'Please fix this', 'Mhaghaed', 'iTunes', 5, 'The app shows blank white screen when you tap on settings', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 06:21:31'),
	(5688, 'I\'ve been trying to train Alexa to my strong Yorkshire accent was told its in settings on app but no options and no update not helpful at all Alexa doesn\'t recognise anything I say it\'s so annoying', 'Craig Neely', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-09 00:00:00'),
