	(5698, 'Alexa became dumb all of a sudden! She can\'t play the next song or stop the music anymore! (Spotify /Sonos combo used to work fine)', 'Clément Chaine', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
	(5699, 'I love my echo. Could use more useful apps. To many non useful apps. I rather the app has a few helpful apps ,then 1,000 non helpful apps.', 'Juan Carrethers', 'GooglePlayStore', 5, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
	(5700, 'Very slow app,  it takes ages to respond. When ever you are trying with different wi-fi connection it\'s horrible to get deducted, sometime we need to relaunch the app xouple of times to configure new wi-fi. No option of adding own playlist and own songs.', 'Maqsood Ahmed', 'GooglePlayStore', 2, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
	(5701, 'Okay update is good but alexa stop short and never finish the sentence at the end.', 'Willis Phillip', 'GooglePlayStore', 4, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
	(5702, 'Why do you have to pay for spotify premium when I can just use my phone or just buy a speaker I just should because for 1 year I can buy my own wow amzon', 'DJ wolf578', 'GooglePlayStore', 3, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
	(5703, 'App is clunky and has a terrible design. It really needs to be rebuilt from the ground up. Voice searching on the echo device for an album I know I have through prime music failed dismally so tired to use the app to search. Wow completely terrible. Just putting a single letter (any letter) into the search box in the music area of the map to search through my music returns no results at all. Let me be clear here, the search function does not work in any way whatsoever. It also fails to sync with some albums I have added so I cannot even manually trawl the hundreds of albums to find the one I\'m looking for. Amazon this is most definitely a failure from you (everything else is awesome though 😂)', 'Barry Ashford', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
	(5704, 'The pits. No longer controls with keyboard input thereby making it impossible for me to control my living room echo from my bedroom without having my bedroom echo respond to commands. Really, a dumbass thing for Amazon to do. You know, sometimes voice activation is not the most desired, appropriate, or even the most convenient way to control an Echo device! Duh!', '', 'GooglePlayStore', 1, '', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-10 00:00:00'),
