	(6028, 'As the title says, I try to open my Alexa app and as the screen loads up, the app crashes and won’t open. I’ve tried everything, deleting, reinstalling, power cycled my phone, made sure I’m all up to date, and yet nothing works... when it does work it’s handy though! So 2/5 for now, until I see that my app works.', 'Metalhead003', 'iTunes', 2, 'App won’t open and crashes when I see a glimpse of hope', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-20 13:09:57'),
	(6029, 'Seriously.. the SLOWEST APP in history. It took me 4 hours (no exaggeration) to FINALLY get Alexa connected to WiFi. And god forbid, take her anywhere. I took her home for a weekend to show my family and it took me another 4 hours to get connected to their WiFi. The shine of her was gone by this point. Honestly, Alexa is collecting dust on my night stand. Thank goodness it was given as a gift and didn’t waste my money on this. But I have hope that updates will be made and improve in the future !', 'iPad/iPhone', 'iTunes', 2, 'App runs on dial up', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-20 13:45:42'),
	(6030, 'App used to work fine with iPhone 7, now with my iPhone X it won’t even open at all.', 'Wolford33', 'iTunes', 1, 'Won’t open', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-20 16:08:15'),
	(6031, 'I haven’t been able to really USE the app in almost a month because of it’s constant crashing! When I open it, it just freezes for at least a minute and then crashes. I’m not able to open any lists, scroll down, nothing!! I thought maybe it was just a fluke and that Amazon would have it fixed within a week, but no! Amazon, if you’re reading this, I’ve been reading other users’ reviews. I’m definitely NOT the only one who has noticed this problem with the app. We are all getting frustrated! When I need to edit or delete a reminder, Alexa tells me to do it through the app... BUT I CAN’T GET ANYWHERE THROUGH THE APP!! It’s so unbelievably frustrating and you guys NEED to fix it ASAP!!! There’s no excuse for this issue lasting as long as it has! Amazon, please fix this before I sell my Echo and get something else!!', 'MissPsyclone', 'iTunes', 1, 'Glitchy AF!!!', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-20 16:40:36'),
	(6032, 'Love Alexa, one problem...frozen screen on app which is on my iPad. Can’t move anything, can’t get lists, can’t get reminders, can’t do anything!  Very frustrating!', 'Pick this', 'iTunes', 1, 'Alexa Show', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-20 16:53:36'),
	(6033, 'Cons: \n-Lack of Fullscreen iPhone X support... this phone has been out for 4 months!\n-Can be buggy sometimes, probably from lack of iPhone X support \n\nPros:\n-Can control Alexa remotely (and my connected lights), which is nice. \n-Allows me to interact with Alexa through a physical platform', 'DemonDestructor', 'iTunes', 3, 'No iPhone X Support', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-20 17:30:53'),
	(6034, 'We use Lists a lot. In the store it takes at least 60 seconds to get to the list and almost that long to refresh when the screen goes dark. Speed this up and I’ll raise my rating.', 'Janet from Cloverdale', 'iTunes', 3, 'App is so slow', 'Amazon Alexa', '2018-02-21 01:26:41');
